obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (15869)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15869&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Patents Act, 1970.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1-4-1978, vide notification No. S.O. 799, dated 10-3-1978, in respect of the provisions of sub-section (2) of s. 12 and`
  line
  line `sub-section (2) of s. 13, s. 28, s. 68, and ss. 125 to 132 see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line
  line `20-4-1972 vide notification No. S.O. 300 dated 20-4-1972, in respect of the provisions [except sub-section (2) of s. 12 and`
  line `sub-section (2) of s. 13, s. 28, s. 68 and ss. 125 to 132] see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (15870)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15870&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1****;
  line
  line `(ab) assignee includes an assignee of the assignee and the legal representative of a deceased`
  line `assignee and references to the assignee of any person include references to the assignee of the legal`
  line `representative or assignee of that person;`
  line
  line `^2[(aba) Budapest Treaty means the Budapest Treaty on the International Recognition of the`
  line `Deposit of Micro-organisms for the purposes of Patent Procedure done at Budapest on 28th day of`
  line `April, 1977, as amended and modified from time to time;]`
  line
  line `(ac) capable of industrial application, in relation to an invention, means that the invention is`
  line `capable of being made or used in an industry;]`
  line
  line `(b) Controller means the Controller General of Patents, Designs and Trade Marks referred to in`
  line `section 73;`
  line
  line `(c) convention application means an application for a patent made by virtue of section 135;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) convention country means a country or a country which is member of a group of countries`
  line `or a union of countries or an Inter-governmental organisation ^4[referred to as a convention country in`
  line `section 133;]`
  line
  line `(e) district court has the meaning assigned to that expression by the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(f) exclusive licence means a licence from a patentee which confers on the licensee, or on the`
  line `licensee and persons authorised by him, to the exclusion of all other persons (including the patentee),`
  line `any right in respect of the patented invention, and exclusive licensee shall be construed`
  line accordingly;
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) Government undertaking means any industrial undertaking carried on--`
  line
  line `(i) by a department of the Government, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a corporation established by a Central, Provincial or State Act, which is owned or`
  line `controlled by the Government, or`
  line
  line `(iii) by a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956),`
  line 1^6[or]
  line
  line `^6[(iv) by an institution wholly or substantially financed by the Government;]`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `^8[(i) High Court, in relation to a State or Union territory, means the High Court having`
  line `territorial jurisdiction in that State or Union territory, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `^9[(ia) international application means an application for patent made in accordance with the`
  line `Patent Cooperation Treaty;]`
  line
  line `^10[(j) invention means a new product or process involving an inventive step and capable of`
  line `industrial application;`
  line
  line `^11[(ja) inventive step means a feature of an invention that involves technical advance as`
  line `compared to the existing knowledge or having economic significance or both and that makes the`
  line `invention not obvious to a person skilled in the art;]]`
  line
  line `(k) legal representative means a person who in law represents the estate of a deceased person;`
  line
  line `^12[(l) new invention means any invention or technology which has not been anticipated by`
  line `publication in any document or used in the country or elsewhere in the world before the date of filing`
  line `of patent application with complete specification, i.e., the subject matter has not fallen in public`
  line `domain or that it does not form part of the state of the art;`
  line
  line `(la) Opposition Board means an Opposition Board constituted under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 25;
  line
  line `(m) patent means a patent for any invention granted under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(n) patent agent means a person for the time being registered under this Act as a patent agent;`
  line
  line `(o) patented article and patented process mean respectively an article or process in respect of`
  line `which a patent is in force;`
  line
  line `^9[(oa) Patent Cooperation Treaty means the Patent Cooperation Treaty done at Washington on`
  line `the 19th day of June, 1970 as amended and modified from time to time;]`
  line
  line `(p) patentee means the person for the time being entered on the register as the grantee or`
  line `proprietor of the patent;`
  line
  line `(q) patent of addition means a patent granted in accordance with section 54;`
  line
  line `(r) patent office means the patent office referred to in section 74;`
  line
  line `(s) person includes the Government;`
  line
  line `(t) person interested includes a person engaged in, or in promoting, research in the same field`
  line `as that to which the invention relates;`
  line
  line `^13[(ta) pharmaceutical substance means any new entity involving one or more inventive steps;]`
  line
  line `^14[(u) prescribed means,--`
  line
  line `(A) in relation to proceedings before a High Court, prescribed by rules made by the High`
  line Court;
  line
  line `^15* * ***;`
  line
  line `(C) in other cases, prescribed by rules made under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(v) prescribed manner includes the payment of the prescribed fee;`
  line
  line `(w) priority date has the meaning assigned to it by section 11;`
  line
  line `(x) register means the register of patents referred to in section 67;`
  line
  line `(y) true and first inventor does not include either the first importer of an invention into India, or`
  line `a person to whom an invention is first communicated from outside India.`
  line
  line `(2) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, any reference--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Controller shall be construed as including a reference to any officer discharging the`
  line `functions of the Controller in pursuance of section 73;`
  line
  line `(b) to the patent office shall be construed as including a reference to any branch office of the`
  line `patent office.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f.4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 3, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 2, for notified as such under sub-section (1) of section 133 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (g) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `7. The words and includes the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research and any other institution which is financed`
  line `wholly or for the major part by the said Council omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (j) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 2, for clause (ja) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clauses (l) and (m) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 3, for clause (u) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `15. Sub-clause (B) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (15871)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `What are not inventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15871&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The following are not inventions within the meaning of this`
  line Act,--
  line
  line `(a) an invention which is frivolous or which claims anything obviously contrary to well`
  line `established natural laws;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) an invention the primary or intended use or commercial exploitation of which would be`
  line `contrary to public order or morality or which causes serious prejudice to human, animal or plant life`
  line `or health or to the environment;]`
  line
  line `(c) the mere discovery of a scientific principle or the formulation of an abstract theory ^2[or`
  line `discovery of any living thing or non-living substance occurring in nature];`
  line
  line `^3[(d) the mere discovery of a new form of a known substance which does not result in the`
  line `enhancement of the known efficacy of that substance or the mere discovery of any new property or`
  line `new use for a known substance or of the mere use of a known process, machine or apparatus unless`
  line `such known process results in a new product or employs at least one new reactant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, salts, esters, ethers, polymorphs, metabolites, pure`
  line `form, particle size, isomers, mixtures of isomers, complexes, combinations and other derivatives of`
  line `known substance shall be considered to be the same substance, unless they differ significantly in`
  line `properties with regard to efficacy;]`
  line
  line `(e) a substance obtained by a mere admixture resulting only in the aggregation of the properties`
  line `of the components thereof or a process for producing such substance;`
  line
  line `(f) the mere arrangement or re-arrangement or duplication of known devices each functioning`
  line `independently of one another in a known way;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) a method of agriculture or horticulture;`
  line
  line `(i) any process for the medicinal, surgical, curative, prophylactic ^5[diagnostic, therapeutic] or`
  line `other treatment of human beings or any process for a similar treatment of animals ^6*** to render them`
  line `free of disease or to increase their economic value or that of their products.`
  line
  line `^5[(j) plants and animals in whole or any part thereof other than micro-organisms but including`
  line `seeds, varieties and species and essentially biological processes for production or propagation of`
  line `plants and animals;`
  line
  line `(k) a mathematical or business method or a computer programme per se or algorithms;`
  line
  line `(l) a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work or any other aesthetic creation whatsoever`
  line `including cinematographic works and television productions;`
  line
  line `(m) a mere scheme or rule or method of performing mental act or method of playing game;`
  line
  line `(n) a presentation of information;`
  line
  line `(o) topography of integrated circuits;`
  line
  line `(p) an invention which, in effect, is traditional knowledge or which is an aggregation or`
  line `duplication of known properties of traditionally known component or components.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 3, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (g) omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `6. The words "or plants" omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (15872)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Inventions relating to atomic energy not patentable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15872&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No patent shall be granted in respect of`
  line `an invention relating to atomic energy falling within sub-section (1) of section 20 of the Atomic Energy`
  line `Act, 1962 (33 of 1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (15873)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15873&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `[Inventions where only methods or`
  line `processes of manufacture patentable.] Omitted by the`
  line `Patents (Amendment) Act, 2005(15 of 2005), s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (15874)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Persons entitled to apply for patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15874&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in section 134, an`
  line `application for a patent for an invention may be made by any of the following persons, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) by any person claiming to be the true and first inventor of the invention;`
  line
  line `(b) by any person being the assignee of the person claiming to be the true and first inventor in`
  line `respect of the right to make such an application;`
  line
  line `(c) by the legal representative of any deceased person who immediately before his death was`
  line `entitled to make such an application.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) may be made by any of the persons referred to therein either`
  line `alone or jointly with any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (15875)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Form of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15875&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for a patent shall be for one invention only and shall`
  line `be made in the prescribed form and filed in the patent office.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Every international application under the Patent Cooperation Treaty for a patent, as may be`
  line `filed designating India, shall be deemed to be an application under this Act, if a corresponding application`
  line `has also been filed before the Controller in India.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1B) The filing date of an application referred to in sub-section (1A) and its complete specification`
  line `processed by the patent office as designated office or elected office shall be the international filing date`
  line `accorded under the Patent Cooperation Treaty.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the application is made by virtue of an assignment of the right to apply for a patent for the`
  line `invention, there shall be furnished with the application, or within such period as may be prescribed after`
  line `the filling of the application, proof of the right to make the application.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under this section shall state that the applicant is in possession of the invention`
  line `and shall name the ^3[person] claiming to be the true and first inventor; and where the person so claiming`
  line `is not the applicant or one of the applicants, the application shall contain a declaration that the applicant`
  line `believes the person so named to be the true and first inventor.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Every such application (not being a convention application or an application filed under the`
  line `Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India) shall be accompanied by a provisional or a complete`
  line specification.]
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "owner" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (15876)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Information and undertaking regarding foreign applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15876&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an applicant for a`
  line `patent under this Act is prosecuting either alone or jointly with any other person an application for a`
  line `patent in any country outside India in respect of the same or substantially the same invention, or where to`
  line `his knowledge such an application is being prosecuted by some person through whom he claims or by`
  line `some person deriving title from him, he shall file along with his application ^1[or subsequently ^2[within the`
  line `prescribed period as the Controller may allow]]--`
  line
  line `^3[(a) a statement setting out detailed particulars of such application; and]`
  line
  line `(b) an undertaking that, ^4[up to the date of grant of patent in India], he would keep the Controller`
  line `informed in writing, from time to time, of ^5[detailed particulars as required under] clause (a) in`
  line `respect of every other application relating to the same or substantially the same invention, if any, filed`
  line `in any country outside India subsequently to the filing of the statement referred to in the aforesaid`
  line `clause within the prescribed time.`
  line
  line `^6[(2) At any time after an application for patent is filed in India and till the grant of a patent or refusal`
  line `to grant of a patent made thereon, the Controller may also require the applicant to furnish details, as may`
  line `be prescribed, relating to the processing of the application in a country outside India, and in that event the`
  line `applicant shall furnish to the Controller information available to him within such period as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 7, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 6, for "upto the date of the acceptance of his complete specification filed in India (w.e.f. 1-1-`
  line `2005).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 7, for "details of the nature referred to in" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (15877)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Provisional and complete specifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15877&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[ (1) Where an application for a patent (not being a`
  line `convention application or an application filed under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India) is`
  line `accompanied by a provisional specification, a complete specification shall be filed within twelve months`
  line `from the date of filing of the application, and if the complete specification is not so filed, the application`
  line `shall be deemed to be abandoned.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where two or more applications in the name of the same applicant are accompanied by`
  line `provisional specifications in respect of inventions which are cognate or of which one is a modification of`
  line `another and the Controller is of opinion that the whole of such inventions are such as to constitute a single`
  line `invention and may properly be included in one patent, he may allow one complete specification to be`
  line `filed in respect of all such provisional specifications:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the period of time specified under sub-section (1) shall be reckoned from the date of`
  line `filing of the earliest provisional specification.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Where an application for a patent (not being a convention application or an application filed`
  line `under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India) is accompanied by a specification purporting to be`
  line `a complete specification, the Controller may, if the applicant so requests at any time within twelve`
  line `months from the date of filing of the application, direct that such specification shall be treated, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, as a provisional specification and proceed with the application accordingly.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where a complete specification has been filed in pursuance of an application for a patent`
  line `accompanied by a provisional specification or by a specification treated by virtue of a direction under`
  line `sub-section (3) as a provisional specification, the Controller may, if the applicant so requests at any time`
  line `before ^4[grant of patent], cancel the provisional specification and post-date the application to the date of`
  line `filing of the complete specification.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "the acceptance of the complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (15878)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Contents of specifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15878&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every specification, whether provisional or complete, shall`
  line `describe the invention and shall begin with a title sufficiently indicating the subject-matter to which the`
  line `invention relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf under this Act, drawings may, and shall, if the`
  line `Controller so requires, be supplied for the purposes of any specification, whether complete or provisional;`
  line `and any drawings so supplied shall, unless the Controller otherwise directs, be deemed to form part of the`
  line `specification, and references in this Act to a specification shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in any particular case, the Controller considers that an application should be further`
  line `supplemented by a model or sample of anything illustrating the invention or alleged to constitute an`
  line `invention, such model or sample as he may require shall be furnished ^1[before the application is found in`
  line `order for grant of a patent], but such model or sample shall not be deemed to form part of the`
  line specification.
  line
  line `(4) Every complete specification shall--`
  line
  line `(a) fully and particularly describe the invention and its operation or use and the method by which`
  line `it is to be performed;`
  line
  line `(b) disclose the best method of performing the invention which is known to the applicant and for`
  line `which he is entitled to claim protection; and`
  line
  line `(c) end with a claim or claims defining the scope of the invention for which protection is claimed.`
  line
  line `^2[(d) be accompanied by an abstract to provide technical information on the invention:`
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) the Controller may amend the abstract for providing better information to third parties; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if the applicant mentions a biological material in the specification which may not be`
  line `described in such a way as to satisfy clauses(a) and (b), and if such material is not available to the`
  line `public, the application shall be completed by depositing ^3[the material to an international`
  line `depository authority under the Budapest Treaty] and by fulfilling the following conditions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `^4[(A) the deposit of the material shall be made not later than the date of filing the patent`
  line `application in India and a reference thereof shall be made in the specification within the`
  line `prescribed period];`
  line
  line `(B) all the available characteristics of the material required for it to be correctly identified`
  line `or indicated are included in the specification including the name, address of the depository`
  line `institution and the date and number of the deposit of the material at the institution;`
  line
  line `(C) access to the material is available in the depository institution only after the date of`
  line `the application for patent in India or if priority is claimed after the date of the priority;`
  line
  line `(D) disclose the source and geographical origin of the biological material in the`
  line `specification, when used in an invention.]`
  line
  line `^5[(4A) Incase of an international application designating India, the title, description, drawings,`
  line `abstract and claims filed with the application shall be taken as the complete specification for the purposes`
  line `of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^6[(5) The claim or claims of a complete specification shall relate to a single invention, or to a group of`
  line `inventions linked so as to form a single inventive concept, shall be clear and succinct and shall be fairly`
  line `based on the matter disclosed in the specification.]`
  line
  line `(6) A declaration as to the inventorship of the invention shall, in such cases as may be prescribed, be`
  line `furnished in the prescribed form with the complete specification or within such period as may be`
  line `prescribed after the filing of that specification.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section, a complete specification filed after a`
  line `provisional specification may include claims in respect of developments of, or additions to, the invention`
  line `which was described in the provisional specification, being developments or additions in respect of which`
  line `the applicant would be entitled under the provisions of section 6 to make a separate application for a`
  line patent.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "before the acceptance of the application" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 8 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 8, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-clause (A) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (4A) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 8, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (15879)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Priority dates of claims of a complete specification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15879&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a priority date for each`
  line `claim of a complete specification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a complete specification is filed in pursuance of a single application accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) a provisional specification; or`
  line
  line `(b) a specification which is treated by virtue of a direction under sub-section (3) of section 9 as a`
  line `provisional specification,`
  line
  line `and the claim is fairly based on the matter disclosed in the specification referred to in clause (a) or clause`
  line `(b), the priority date of that claim shall be the date of the filing of the relevant specification.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the complete specification is filed or proceeded with in pursuance of two or more`
  line `applications accompanied by such specifications as are mentioned in sub-section (2) and the claim is`
  line `fairly based on the matter disclosed--`
  line
  line `(a) in one of those specifications, the priority date of that claim shall be the date of the filing of`
  line `the application accompanied by that specification;`
  line
  line `(b) partly in one and partly in another, the priority date of that claim shall be the date of the filing`
  line `of the application accompanied by the specification of the later date.`
  line
  line `^1[(3A) Where a complete specification based on a previously filed application in India has been filed`
  line `within twelve months from the date of that application and the claim is fairly based on the matter`
  line `disclosed in the previously filed application, the priority date of that claim shall be the date of the`
  line `previously filed application in which the matter was first disclosed.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where the complete specification has been filed in pursuance of a further application made by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (1) of section 16 and the claim is fairly based on the matter disclosed in any of the`
  line `earlier specifications, provisional or complete, as the case may be, the priority date of that claim shall be`
  line `the date of the filing of that specification in which the matter was first disclosed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, under the foregoing provisions of this section, any claim of a complete specification`
  line `would, but for the provisions of this sub-section, have two or more priority dates, the priority date of that`
  line `claim shall be the earlier or earliest of those dates.`
  line
  line `(6) In any case to which sub-sections (2), (3), ^1[(3A)], (4) and (5) do not apply, the priority date of a`
  line `claim shall, subject to the provisions of section 137, be the date of filing of the complete specification.`
  line
  line `(7) The reference to the date of the filing of the application or of the complete specification in this`
  line `section shall, in cases where there has been a post-dating under section 9 or section 17 or, as the case may`
  line `be, ante-dating under section 16, be a reference to the date as so post-dated or ante-dated.`
  line
  line `(8) A claim in a complete specification of a patent shall not be invalid by reason only of--`
  line
  line `(a) the publication or use of the invention so far as claimed in that claim on or after the priority`
  line `date of such claim; or`
  line
  line `(b) the grant of another patent which claims the invention, so far as claimed in the first mentioned`
  line `claim, in a claim of the same or a later priority date.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (15880)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Publication of applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15880&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 , ^2[11A. Publication of applications.-- ^3[(1) Save as otherwise provided, no application for patent`
  line `shall ordinarily be opened to the public for such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The applicant may, in the prescribed manner, request the Controller to publish his application at`
  line `any time before the expiry of the period prescribed under sub-section (1) and subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), the Controller shall publish such application as soon as possible.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for a patent shall, on the expiry of the period specified under sub-section (1), be`
  line `published, except in cases where the application--`
  line
  line `(a) in which secrecy direction is imposed under section 35; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been abandoned under sub-section (1) of section 9; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been withdrawn three months prior to the period specified under sub-section (1)].`
  line
  line `(4) In case a secrecy direction has been given in respect of an application under section 35, then, it`
  line `shall be published after the expiry of the period ^4[prescribed under sub-section (1)] or when the secrecy`
  line `direction has ceased to operate, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(5) The publication of every application under this section shall include the particulars of the date of`
  line `application, number of application, name and address of the applicant identifying the application and an`
  line abstract.
  line
  line `(6) Upon publication of an application for a patent under this section--`
  line
  line `(a) the depository institution shall make the biological material mentioned in the specification`
  line `available to the public;`
  line
  line `(b) the patent office may, on payment of such fee as may be prescribed, make the specification`
  line `and drawings, if any, of such application available to the public.`
  line
  line `^5[(7) On and from the date of publication of the application for patent and until the date of grant of a`
  line `patent in respect of such application, the applicant shall have the like privileges and rights as if a patent`
  line `for the invention had been granted on the date of publication of the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the applicant shall not be entitled to institute any proceedings for infringement until the`
  line `patent has been granted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the rights of a patentee in respect of applications made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5 before the 1st day of January, 2005 shall accrue from the date of grant of the patent:`
  line
  line `Provided also that after a patent is granted in respect of applications made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5, the patent-holder shall only be entitled to receive reasonable royalty from such enterprises`
  line `which have made significant investment and were producing and marketing the concerned product prior`
  line `to the 1st day of January, 2005 and which continue to manufacture the product covered by the patent on`
  line `the date of grant of the patent and no infringement proceedings shall be instituted against such`
  line enterprises.]
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 9, for the Chapter heading "EXAMINATION OF APPLICATION" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 10, for sub-sections (1) to (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 10, for "of eighteen months" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (15881)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 13
  title `Request for examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15881&sectionno=11B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Request for examination.--^2[(1) No application for a patent shall be examined unless the`
  line `applicant or any other interested person makes a request in the prescribed manner for such examination`
  line `within the prescribed period.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(3) In case of an application in respect of a claim for a patent filed under sub-section (2) of section 5`
  line `before the 1st day of January, 2005 a request for its examination shall be made in the prescribed manner`
  line `and within the prescribed period by the applicant or any other interested person.]`
  line
  line `(4) In case the applicant or any other interested person does not make a request for examination of the`
  line `application for a patent within the period as specified under sub-section (1)^5***`
  line `or sub-section (3), the`
  line `application shall be treated as withdrawn by the applicant:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) the applicant may, at any time after filing the application but before the grant of a patent,`
  line `withdraw the application by making a request in the prescribed manner; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case where secrecy direction has been issued under section 35, the request for`
  line `examination may be made within the prescribed period from the date of revocation of the secrecy`
  line direction.]
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. The words, brackets and figure "or sub-section (2)" omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (15882)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Examination of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15882&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) When a request for examination has been made in respect`
  line `of an application for a patent in the prescribed manner ^2[under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 11B, the application and specification and other documents related thereto shall be referred at the`
  line `earliest by the Controller] to an examiner for making a report to him in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) whether the application and the ^3[specification and other documents relating thereto] are in`
  line `accordance with the requirements of this Act and of any rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) whether there is any lawful ground of objection to the grant of the patent under this Act in`
  line `pursuance of the application;`
  line
  line `(c) the result of investigations made under section 13; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The examiner to whom the application and the ^3[specification and other documents relating`
  line `thereto] are referred under sub-section (1) shall ordinarily make the report to the Controller within ^4[such`
  line `period as may be prescribed].`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 10, for certain words (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 12, for certain words, brackets, figures and letter (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 10, for "specification relating thereto" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 12, for "a period of eighteen months from the date of such reference" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (15883)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Search for anticipation by previous publication and by prior claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15883&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The examiner to`
  line `whom an application for a patent is referred under section 12 shall make investigation for the purpose of`
  line `ascertaining whether the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification--`
  line
  line `(a) has been anticipated by publication before the date of filing of the applicant's complete`
  line `specification in any specification filed in pursuance of an application for a patent made in India and`
  line `dated on or after the 1st day of January, 1912;`
  line
  line `(b) is claimed in any claim of any other complete specification published on or after the date of`
  line `filing of the applicant's complete specification, being a specification filed in pursuance of an`
  line `application for a patent made in India and dated before or claiming the priority date earlier than that`
  line date.
  line
  line `(2) The examiner shall, in addition, make such investigation ^1*** for the purpose of ascertaining`
  line `whether the invention, so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification, has been anticipated`
  line `by publication in India or elsewhere in any document other than those mentioned in sub-section (1) before`
  line `the date of filing of the applicants complete specification.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a complete specification is amended under the provisions of this Act before ^2[the grant of a`
  line `a patent], the amended specification shall be examined and investigated in like manner as the original`
  line specification.
  line
  line `(4) The examination and investigations required under section 12 and this section shall not be deemed`
  line `in any way to warrant the validity of any patent, and no liability shall be incurred by the Central`
  line `Government or any officer thereof by reason of, or in connection with, any such examination or`
  line `investigation or any report or other proceedings consequent thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "as the Controller may direct" omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 11 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2 . Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 13, for "it has been accepted" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (15884)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Consideration of report of examiner by Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15884&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Consideration of report of examiner by Controller.-- Where, in respect of an application for`
  line `a patent, the report of the examiner received by the Controller is adverse to the applicant or requires any`
  line `amendment of the application, the specification or other documents to ensure compliance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of the rules made thereunder, the Controller, before proceeding to dispose of the`
  line `application in accordance with the provisions hereinafter appearing, shall communicate as expeditiously`
  line `as possible the gist of the objections to the applicant and shall, if so required by the applicant within the`
  line `prescribed period, give him an opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (15885)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Controller to refuse or require amended applications, etc., in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15885&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Power of Controller to refuse or require amended applications, etc., in certain cases.--Where the Controller is satisfied that the application or any specification or any other document filed in`
  line `pursuance thereof does not comply with the requirements of this Act or of any rules made thereunder, the`
  line `Controller may refuse the application or may require the application, specification or the other`
  line `documents, as the case may be, to be amended to his satisfaction before he proceeds with the application`
  line `and refuse the application on failure to do so.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (15886)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Controller to make orders respecting division of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15886&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who`
  line `has made an application for a patent under this Act may, at any time ^1[before the grant of the patent], if he`
  line `so desires, or with a view to remedy the objection raised by the Controller on the ground that the claims`
  line `of the complete specification relate to more than one invention, file a further application in respect of an`
  line `invention disclosed in the provisional or complete specification already filed in respect of the first`
  line `mentioned application.`
  line
  line `(2) The further application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a complete specification,`
  line `but such complete specification shall not include any matter not in substance disclosed in the complete`
  line `specification filed in pursuance of the first mentioned application.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller may require such amendment of the complete specification filed in pursuance of`
  line `either the original or the further application as may be necessary to ensure that neither of the said`
  line `complete specifications includes a claim for any matter claimed in the other.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Act, the further application and the complete specification`
  line `accompanying it shall be deemed to have been filed on the date on which the first mentioned application`
  line `had been filed, and the further application shall be proceeded with as a substantive application and be`
  line `examined when the request for examination is filed within the prescribed period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 15, for "before the acceptance of the complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (15887)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Controller to make orders respecting dating of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15887&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 9, at any time after the filing of an application and ^1[before the grant of the patent]`
  line `under this Act, the Controller may, at the request of the applicant made in the prescribed manner, direct`
  line `that the application shall be post-dated to such date as may be specified in the request, and proceed with`
  line `the application accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be post-dated under this sub-section to a date later than six months`
  line `from the date on which it was actually made or would, but for the provisions of this sub-section, be`
  line `deemed to have been made.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where an application or specification (including drawings) or any other documents is required to`
  line `to be amended under section 15, the application or specification or other document shall, if the Controller`
  line `so directs, be deemed to have been made on the date on which the requirement is complied with or where`
  line `the application or specification or other document is returned to the applicant, on the date on which it is`
  line `refiled after complying with the requirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "before the acceptance of the complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 13, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (15888)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers of Controller in cases of anticipation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15888&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Controller that the`
  line `invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification has been anticipated in the manner`
  line `referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 13, he may refuse to ^1[the`
  line `application] unless the applicant--`
  line
  line `(a) shows to the satisfaction of the Controller that the priority date of the claim of his complete`
  line `specification is not later than the date on which the relevant document was published; or`
  line
  line `(b) amends his complete specification to the satisfaction of the Controller.`
  line
  line `(2) If it appears to the Controller that the invention is claimed in a claim of any other complete`
  line `specification referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 13, he may, subject to the provisions`
  line `hereinafter contained, direct that a reference to that other specification shall be inserted by way of notice`
  line `to the public in the applicants complete specification unless within such time as may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant shows to the satisfaction of the Controller that the priority date of his claim is`
  line `not later than the priority date of the claim of the said other specification; or`
  line
  line `(b) the complete specification is amended to the satisfaction of the Controller.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to the Controller, as a result of an investigation under section 13 or otherwise,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the applicant's complete specification has`
  line `been claimed in any other complete specification referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `13; and`
  line
  line `(b) that such other complete specification was published on or after the priority date of the`
  line `applicant's claim,`
  line
  line `then, unless it is shown to the satisfaction of the Controller that the priority date of the applicant's claim is`
  line `not later than the priority date of the claim of that specification, the provisions of sub-section (2) shall`
  line `apply thereto in the same manner as they apply to a specification published on or after the date of filing of`
  line `the applicant's complete specification.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 17, for "to accept the complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (4) omitted by Act 15 of 2005, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (15889)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Powers of Controller in case of potential infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "by the foregoing provisions of this Act or of proceedings under section 25" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15889&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in consequence of the`
  line `investigations required ^1[under this Act], it appears to the Controller that an invention in respect of which`
  line `an application for a patent has been made cannot be performed without substantial risk of infringement of`
  line `a claim of any other patent, he may direct that a reference to that other patent shall be inserted in the`
  line `applicant's complete specification by way of notice to the public, unless within such time as may be`
  line prescribed--
  line
  line `(a) the applicant shows to the satisfaction of the Controller that there are reasonable grounds for`
  line `contesting the validity of the said claim of the other patent; or`
  line
  line `(b) the complete specification is amended to the satisfaction of the Controller.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, after a reference to another patent has been inserted in a complete specification in`
  line `pursuance of a direction under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) that other patent is revoked or otherwise ceases to be in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) the specification of that other patent is amended by the deletion of the relevant claim; or`
  line
  line `(c) it is found, in proceedings before the court or the Controller, that the relevant claim of that`
  line `other patent is invalid or is not infringed by any working of the applicant's invention, the Controller`
  line `may, on the application of the applicant, delete the reference to that other patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (15890)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers of Controller to make orders regarding substitution of applicants etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15890&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `Controller is satisfied, on a claim made in the prescribed manner at any time before a patent has been`
  line `granted, that by virtue of any assignment or agreement in writing made by the applicant or one of the`
  line `applicants for the patent or by operation of law, the claimant would, if the patent were then granted be`
  line `entitled thereto or to the interest of the applicant therein, or to an undivided share of the patent or of that`
  line `interest, the Controller may, subject to the provisions of this section, direct that the application shall`
  line `proceed in the name of the claimant or in the names of the claimants and the applicant or the other joint`
  line `applicant or applicants, accordingly as the case may require.`
  line
  line `(2) No such direction as aforesaid shall be given by virtue of any assignment or agreement made by`
  line `one of two or more joint applicants for a patent except with the consent of the other joint applicant or`
  line applicants.
  line
  line `(3) No such direction as aforesaid shall be given by virtue of any assignment or agreement for the`
  line `assignment of the benefit of an invention unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the invention is identified therein by reference to the number of the application for the patent;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) there is produced to the Controller an acknowledgment by the person by whom the`
  line `assignment or agreement was made that the assignment or agreement relates to the invention in`
  line `respect of which that application is made; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rights of the claimant in respect of the invention have been finally established by the`
  line `decision of a court; or`
  line
  line `(d) the Controller gives directions for enabling the application to proceed or for regulating the`
  line `manner in which it should be proceeded with under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(4) Where one of two or more joint applicants for a patent dies at any time before the patent has been`
  line `granted, the Controller may, upon a request in that behalf made by the survivor or survivors, and with the`
  line `consent of the legal representative of the deceased, direct that the application shall proceed in the name of`
  line `the survivor or survivors alone.`
  line
  line `(5) If any dispute arises between joint applicants for a patent whether or in what manner the`
  line `application should be proceeded with, the Controller may, upon application made to him in the prescribed`
  line `manner by any of the parties, and after giving to all parties concerned an opportunity to be heard, give`
  line `such directions as he thinks fit for enabling the application to proceed in the name of one or more of the`
  line `parties alone or for regulating the manner in which it should be proceeded with, or for both those`
  line `purposes, as the case may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (15891)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Time for putting application in order for grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 19, for section 21 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15891&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Time for putting application in order for grant.-- (1) An application for a patent shall be`
  line `deemed to have been abandoned unless, within such period as may be prescribed, the applicant has`
  line `complied with all the requirements imposed on him by or under this Act, whether in connection with the`
  line `complete specification or otherwise in relation to the application from the date on which the first`
  line `statement of objections to the application or complete specification or other documents related thereto is`
  line `forwarded to the applicant by the Controller.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where the application for a patent or any specification or, in the case of a convention`
  line `application or an application filed under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India any document`
  line `filed as part of the application has been returned to the applicant by the Controller in the course of the`
  line `proceedings, the applicant shall not be deemed to have complied with such requirements unless and until`
  line `he has refiled it or the applicant proves to the satisfaction of the Controller that for the reasons beyond his`
  line `control such document could not be refiled.`
  line
  line `(2) If at the expiration of the period as prescribed under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) an appeal to the High Court is pending in respect of the application for the patent for the main`
  line `invention; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an application for a patent of addition, an appeal to the High Court is pending in`
  line `respect of either that application or the application for the main invention, the time within which the`
  line `requirements of the Controller shall be complied with shall, on an application made by the applicant`
  line `before the expiration of the period as prescribed under sub-section (1), be extended until such date as`
  line `the High Court may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) If the time within which the appeal mentioned in sub-section (2) may be instituted has not expired,`
  line `the Controller may extend the period as prescribed under sub-section (1), to such further period as he may`
  line `determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an appeal has been filed during the said further period, and the High Court has`
  line `granted any extension of time for complying with the requirements of the Controller, then the`
  line `requirements may be complied with within the time granted by the Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (15892)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15892&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
