obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (15895)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Opposition to patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15895&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1,^2[25. Opposition to the patent.-- (1) Where an application for a patent has been published but a`
  line `patent has not been granted, any person may, in writing, represent by way of opposition to the Controller`
  line `against the grant of patent on the ground--`
  line
  line `(a) that the applicant for the patent or the person under or through whom he claims, wrongfully`
  line `obtained the invention or any part thereof from him or from a person under or through whom he`
  line claims;
  line
  line `(b) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification has been`
  line `published before the priority date of the claim--`
  line
  line `(i) in any specification filed in pursuance of an application for a patent made in India on or`
  line `after the 1st day of January, 1912; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in India or elsewhere, in any other document:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ground specified in sub-clause (ii) shall not be available where such`
  line `publication does not constitute an anticipation of the invention by virtue of sub-section (2) or subsection`
  line `(3) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(c) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is claimed in a`
  line `claim of a complete specification published on or after the priority date of the applicant's claim and`
  line `filed in pursuance of an application for a patent in India, being a claim of which the priority date is`
  line `earlier than that of the applicants claim;`
  line
  line `(d) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was publicly`
  line `known or publicly used in India before the priority date of that claim.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, an invention relating to a process for which a`
  line `patent is claimed shall be deemed to have been publicly known or publicly used in India before the`
  line `priority date of the claim if a product made by that process had already been imported into India`
  line `before that date except where such importation has been for the purpose of reasonable trial or`
  line `experiment only;`
  line
  line `(e) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is obvious and`
  line `clearly does not involve any inventive step, having regard to the matter published as mentioned in`
  line `clause (b) or having regard to what was used in India before the priority date of the applicant's claim;`
  line
  line `(f) that the subject of any claim of the complete specification is not an invention within the`
  line `meaning of this Act, or is not patentable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) that the complete specification does not sufficiently and clearly describe the invention or the`
  line `method by which it is to be performed;`
  line
  line `(h) that the applicant has failed to disclose to the Controller the information required by section 8`
  line `or has furnished the information which in any material particular was false to his knowledge;`
  line
  line `(i) that in the case of a convention application, the application was not made within twelve`
  line `months from the date of the first application for protection for the invention made in a convention`
  line `country by the applicant or a person from whom he derives title;`
  line
  line `(j) that the complete specification does not disclose or wrongly mentions the source or`
  line `geographical origin of biological material used for the invention;`
  line
  line `(k) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is anticipated`
  line `having regard to the knowledge, oral or otherwise, available within any local or indigenous`
  line `community in India or elsewhere,`
  line
  line `but on no other ground and the Controller shall, if requested by such person for being heard, hear him and`
  line `dispose of such representation in such manner and within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) At any time after the grant of patent but before the expiry of a period of one year from the date of`
  line `publication of grant of a patent, any person interested may give notice of opposition to the Controller in`
  line `the prescribed manner on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the patentee or the person under or through whom he claims, wrongfully obtained the`
  line `invention or any part thereof from him or from a person under or through whom he claims;`
  line
  line `(b) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification has been`
  line `published before the priority date of the claim--`
  line
  line `(i) in any specification filed in pursuance of an application for a patent made in India on or`
  line `after the 1st day of January, 1912; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in India or elsewhere, in any other document:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ground specified in sub-clause (ii) shall not be available where such`
  line `publication does not constitute an anticipation of the invention by virtue of sub-section (2) or subsection`
  line `(3) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(c) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is claimed in a`
  line `claim of a complete specification published on or after the priority date of the claim of the patentee`
  line `and filed in pursuance of an application for a patent in India, being a claim of which the priority date`
  line `is earlier than that of the claim of the patentee;`
  line
  line `(d) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was publicly`
  line `known or publicly used in India before the priority date of that claim.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, an invention relating to a process for which a`
  line `patent is granted shall be deemed to have been publicly known or publicly used in India before the`
  line `priority date of the claim if a product made by that process had already been imported into India`
  line `before that date except where such importation has been for the purpose of reasonable trial or`
  line `experiment only;`
  line
  line `(e) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is obvious and`
  line `clearly does not involve any inventive step, having regard to the matter published as mentioned in`
  line `clause (b) or having regard to what was used in India before the priority date of the claim;`
  line
  line `(f) that the subject of any claim of the complete specification is not an invention within the`
  line `meaning of this Act, or is not patentable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) that the complete specification does not sufficiently and clearly describe the invention or the`
  line `method by which it is to be performed;`
  line
  line `(h) that the patentee has failed to disclose to the Controller the information required by section 8`
  line `or has furnished the information which in any material particular was false to his knowledge;`
  line
  line `(i) that in the case of a patent granted on convention application, the application for patent was`
  line `not made within twelve months from the date of the first application for protection for the invention`
  line `made in a convention country or in India by the patentee or a person from whom he derives title;`
  line
  line `(j) that the complete specification does not disclose or wrongly mentions the source and`
  line `geographical origin of biological material used for the invention;`
  line
  line `(k) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was anticipated`
  line `having regard to the knowledge, oral or otherwise, available within any local or indigenous`
  line `community in India or elsewhere,`
  line
  line `but on no other ground.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) Where any such notice of opposition is duly given under sub-section (2), the Controller shall`
  line `notify the patentee.`
  line
  line `(b) On receipt of such notice of opposition, the Controller shall, by order in writing, constitute a`
  line `Board to be known as the Opposition Board consisting of such officers as he may determine and refer`
  line `such notice of opposition along with the documents to that Board for examination and submission of its`
  line `recommendations to the Controller.`
  line
  line `(c) Every Opposition Board constituted under clause (b) shall conduct the examination in accordance`
  line `with such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of the recommendation of the Opposition Board and after giving the patentee and the`
  line `opponent an opportunity of being heard, the Controller shall order either to maintain or to amend or to`
  line `revoke the patent.`
  line
  line `(5) While passing an order under sub-section (4) in respect of the ground mentioned in clause (d) or`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (2), the Controller shall not take into account any personal document or secret`
  line `trial or secret use.`
  line
  line `(6) In case the Controller issues an order under sub-section (4) that the patent shall be maintained`
  line `subject to amendment of the specification or any other document, the patent shall stand amended`
  line accordingly.]
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for Chapter Heading (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for sections 25 and 26 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (15896)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `In cases of "obtaining" Controller may treat the patent as the patent of opponent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for sections 25 and 26 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15896&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. In cases of “obtaining” Controller may treat the patent as the patent of opponent.--(1)`
  line `Where in any opposition proceeding under this Act the Controller finds that--`
  line
  line `(a) the invention, so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification, was obtained from`
  line `the opponent in the manner set out in clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 25 and revokes the`
  line `patent on that ground, he may, on request by such opponent made in the prescribed manner, direct`
  line `that the patent shall stand amended in the name of the opponent;`
  line
  line `(b) a part of an invention described in the complete specification was so obtained from the`
  line `opponent, he may pass an order requiring that the specification be amended by the exclusion of that`
  line `part of the invention.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an opponent has, before the date of the order of the Controller requiring the amendment of`
  line `a complete specification referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1), filed an application for a patent for an`
  line `invention which included the whole or a part of the invention held to have been obtained from him and`
  line `such application is pending, the Controller may treat such application and specification in so far as they`
  line `relate to the invention held to have been obtained from him, as having been filed, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act relating to the priority dates of claims of the complete specification, on the date on which the`
  line `corresponding document was or was deemed to have been filed by the patentee in the earlier application`
  line `but for all other purposes the application of the opponent shall be proceeded with as an application for a`
  line `patent under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (15897)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15897&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `[Refusal of patent without opposition.]--Omitted by the Patents (Amendment) Act, 2005 (15 of`
  line `2005), s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (15898)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Mention of inventor as such in patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15898&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Controller is satisfied, upon a request or`
  line `claim made in accordance with the provisions of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the person in respect of or by whom the request or claim is made is the inventor of an`
  line `invention in respect of which application for a patent has been made, or of a substantial part of that`
  line `invention; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the application for the patent is a direct consequence of his being the inventor,`
  line `the Controller shall, subject to the provisions of this section, cause him to be mentioned as inventor in any`
  line `patent granted in pursuance of the application in the complete specification and in the register of Patents:`
  line
  line `Provided that the mention of any person as inventor under this section shall not confer or derogate`
  line `from any rights under the patent.`
  line
  line `(2) A request that any person shall be mentioned as aforesaid may be made in the prescribed manner`
  line `by the applicant for the patent or (where the person alleged to be the inventor is not the applicant or one`
  line `of the applicants) by the applicant and that person.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person [other than a person in respect of whom a request in relation to the application in`
  line `question has been made under sub-section (2)] desires to be mentioned as aforesaid, he may make a claim`
  line `in the prescribed manner in that behalf.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) A request or claim under the foregoing provisions of this section shall be made before the grant`
  line `of patent.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(6) ^3[Where] a claim is made under sub-section (3), the Controller shall give notice of the claim to`
  line `every applicant for the patent (not being the claimant) and to any other person whom the Controller may`
  line `consider to be interested;`
  line `and before deciding upon any request or claim made under sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), the Controller shall, if required, hear the person in respect of or by whom the request or`
  line `claim is made, and, in the case of a claim under sub-section (3), any person to whom notice of the claim`
  line `has been given as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any person has been mentioned as inventor in pursuance of this section anyother person`
  line `who alleges that he ought not to have been so mentioned may at any time apply to the Controller for a`
  line `certificate to that effect, and the Controller may, after hearing, if required, any person whom he may`
  line `consider to be interested, issue such a certificate, and if he does so, he shall rectify the specification and`
  line `the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 25, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (5) omitted by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), where" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (15899)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Anticipation by previous publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15899&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) An invention claimed in a complete specification`
  line `shall not be deemed to have been anticipated by reason only that the invention was published in a`
  line `specification filed in pursuance of an application for a patent made in India and dated before the 1st day`
  line `of January, 1912.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject as hereinafter provided, an invention claimed in a complete specification shall not be`
  line `deemed to have been anticipated by reason only that the invention was published before the priority date`
  line `of the relevant claim of the specification, if the patentee or the applicant for the patent proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that the matter published was obtained from him, or (where he is not himself the true and first`
  line `inventor) from any person from whom he derives title, and was published without his consent or the`
  line `consent of any such person; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the patentee or the applicant for the patent or any person from whom he derives title`
  line `learned of the publication before the date of the application for the patent, or, in the case of a`
  line `convention application, before the date of the application for protection in a convention country, that`
  line `the application or the application in the convention country, as the case may be, was made as soon as`
  line `reasonably practicable thereafter:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply if the invention was before the priority date of the claim`
  line `commercially worked in India, otherwise than for the purpose of reasonable trial, either by the patentee or`
  line `the applicant for the patent or any person from whom he derives title or by any other person with the`
  line `consent of the patentee or the applicant for the patent or any person from whom he derives title.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a complete specification is filed in pursuance of an application for a patent made by a`
  line `person being the true and first inventor or deriving title from him, an invention claimed in that`
  line `specification shall not be deemed to have been anticipated by reason only of any other application for a`
  line `patent in respect of the same invention made in contravention of the rights of that person, or by reason`
  line `only that after the date of filing of that other application the invention was used or published, without the`
  line `consent of that person, by the applicant in respect of that other application or by any other person in`
  line `consequence of any disclosure of any invention by that applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (15900)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Anticipation by previous communication to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15900&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `An invention claimed in a`
  line `complete specification shall not be deemed to have been anticipated by reason only of the communication`
  line `of the invention to the Government or to any person authorised by the Government to investigate the`
  line `invention or its merits, or of anything done, in consequence of such a communication, for the purpose of`
  line `the investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (15901)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Anticipation by public display, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 26, for "not later than six months" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15901&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `An invention claimed in a complete specification shall not`
  line `be deemed to have been anticipated by reason only of--`
  line
  line `(a) the display of the invention with the consent of the true and first inventor or a person deriving`
  line `title from him at an industrial or other exhibition to which the provisions of this section have been`
  line `extended by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette, or the use thereof with`
  line `his consent for the purpose of such an exhibition in the place where it is held; or`
  line
  line `(b) the publication of any description of the invention in consequence of the display or use of the`
  line `invention at any such exhibition as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(c) the use of the invention, after it has been displayed or used at any such exhibition as aforesaid`
  line `and during the period of the exhibition, by any person without the consent of the true and first`
  line `inventor or a person deriving title from him; or`
  line
  line `(d) the description of the invention in a paper read by the true and first inventor before a learned`
  line `society or published with his consent in the transactions of such a society,`
  line
  line `if the application for the patent is made by the true and first inventor or a person deriving title from him`
  line `^1[not later than twelve months] after the opening of the exhibition or the reading or publication of the`
  line `paper, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (15902)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Anticipation by public working.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15902&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `An invention claimed in a complete specification shall not be`
  line `deemed to have been anticipated by reason only that at any time within one year before the priority date`
  line `of the relevant claim of the specification, the invention was publicly worked in India--`
  line
  line `(a) by the patentee or applicant for the patent or any person from whom he derives title; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any other person with the consent of the patentee or applicant for the patent or any person`
  line `from whom he derives title,`
  line
  line `if the working was effected for the purpose of reasonable trial only and if it was reasonably necessary,`
  line `having regard to the nature of the invention, that the working for that purpose should be effected in`
  line public.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (15903)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Anticipation by use and publication after provisional specification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15903&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a complete`
  line `specification is filed or proceeded with in pursuance of an application which was accompanied by a`
  line `provisional specification or where a complete specification filed along with an application is treated by`
  line `virtue of a direction under sub-section (3) of section 9 as a provisional specification, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Controller shall not refuse to grant the patent, and the`
  line `patent shall not be revoked or invalidated, by reason only that any matter described in the provisional`
  line `specification or in the specification treated as aforesaid as a provisional specification was used in India or`
  line `published in India or elsewhere at any time after the date of the filing of that specification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a complete specification is filed in pursuance of a convention application, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Controller shall not refuse to grant the patent, and the`
  line `patent shall not be revoked or invalidated, by reason only that any matter disclosed in any application for`
  line `protection in a convention country upon which the convention application is founded was used in India or`
  line `published in India or elsewhere at any time after the date of that application for protection.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (15904)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `No anticipation if circumstances are only as described in sections 29, 30, 31 and 32.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. The words "to accept complete specification for a patent or" omitted by Act 15 of 2005, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15904&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act, the Controller shall not refuse ^1*** to grant a`
  line `patent, and a patent shall not be revoked or invalidated by reason only of any circumstances which, by`
  line `virtue of section 29 or section 30 or section 31 or section 32, do not constitute an anticipation of the`
  line `invention claimed in the specification.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (15905)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Secrecy directions relating to inventions relevant for defence purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15905&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in`
  line `respect of an application made before or after the commencement of this Act for a patent, it appears to the`
  line `Controller that the invention is one of a class notified to him by the Central Government as relevant for`
  line `defence purposes, or, where otherwise the invention appears to him to be so relevant, he may give`
  line `directions for prohibiting or restricting the publication of information with respect to the invention or the`
  line `communication of such information ^1***.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Controller gives any such directions as are referred to in sub-section (1), he shall give`
  line `notice of the application and of the directions to the Central Government, and the Central Government`
  line `shall, upon receipt of such notice, consider whether the publication of the invention would be prejudicial`
  line `to the defence of India, and if upon such consideration, it appears to it that the publication of the invention`
  line `would not so prejudice, give notice to the Controller to that effect, who shall thereupon revoke the`
  line `directions and notify the applicant accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), where the Central Government`
  line `is of opinion that an invention in respect of which the Controller has not given any directions under`
  line `sub-section (1), is relevant for defence purposes, it may at any time before ^2[grant of patent] notify the`
  line `Controller to that effect, and thereupon the provisions of that sub-section shall apply as if the invention`
  line `were one of the class notified by the Central Government, and accordingly the Controller shall give notice`
  line `to the Central Government of the directions issued by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "to any person or class of persons specified in the directions" omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 19 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 28, for "acceptance of complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (15906)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Secrecy directions to be periodically reviewed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15906&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The question whether an invention in`
  line `respect of which directions have been given under section 35 continues to be relevant for defence`
  line `purposes shall be reconsidered by the Central Government at intervals of ^2[six months] or on a request`
  line `made by the applicant which is found to be reasonable by the Controller and if, on such reconsideration it`
  line `appears to the Central Government that the publication of the invention would no longer be prejudicial to`
  line `the defence of India or in case of an application filed by a foreign applicant it is found that the invention`
  line `is published outside India it shall forthwith give notice to the Controller to revoke the direction and the`
  line `Controllers shall thereupon revoke the directions previously given by him.]`
  line
  line `(2) The result of every re-consideration under sub-section (1), shall be communicated to the applicant`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 20, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 29, for "twelve months" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (15907)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Consequences of secrecy directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15907&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) So long as any directions under section 35 are in force`
  line `in respect of an application--`
  line
  line `(a) the Controller shall not pass an order refusing ^1[to grant] the same; and`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no appeal shall lie from any order of the`
  line `Controller passed in respect thereof:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the application may, subject to the directions, proceed up to the stage of grant of the`
  line `patent, but the application and the specification found to be in order for grant of the patent shall not be`
  line `published, and no patent shall be granted in pursuance of that application.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where a complete specification filed in pursuance of an application for a patent for an invention`
  line `in respect of which directions have been given under section 35 ^3[is found to be in order for grant of the`
  line `patent] during the continuance in force of the directions, then--`
  line
  line `(a) if, during the continuance in force of the directions, any use of the invention is made by or on`
  line `behalf of, or to the order of the Government, the provisions of sections 100, 101 and 103 shall apply`
  line `in relation to that use as if the patent had been granted for the invention ; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it appears to the Central Government that the applicant for the patent has suffered hardship`
  line `by reason of the continuance in force of the directions, the Central Government may make to him`
  line `such payment (if any) by way of solatium as appears to the Central Government to be reasonable`
  line `having regard to the novelty and utility of the invention and the purpose for which it is designed, and`
  line `to any other relevant circumstances.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a patent is granted in pursuance of an application in respect of which directions have been`
  line `given under section 35, no renewal fee shall be payable in respect of any period during which those`
  line `directions were in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "to accept" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 30, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "is accepted" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (15908)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Revocation of secrecy directions and extension of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15908&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `When any direction given under`
  line `section 35 is revoked by the Controller, then, notwithstanding any provision of this Act specifying the`
  line `time within which any step should be taken or any act done in connection with an application for the`
  line `patent, the Controller may, subject to such conditions, if any, as he thinks fit to impose, extend the time`
  line `for doing anything required or authorised to be done by or under this Act in connection with the`
  line `application, whether or not that time has previously expired.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (15909)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Residents not to apply for patents outside India without prior permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by s. 31, ibid., for section 39 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15909&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Residents not to apply for patents outside India without prior permission.--(1) No person`
  line `resident in India shall, except under the authority of a written permit sought in the manner prescribed and`
  line `granted by or on behalf of the Controller, make or cause to be made any application outside India for the`
  line `grant of a patent for an invention unless--`
  line
  line `(a) an application for a patent for the same invention has been made in India, not less than six`
  line `weeks before the application outside India; and`
  line
  line `(b) either no direction has been given under sub-section (1) of section 35 in relation to the`
  line `application in India, or all such directions have been revoked.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall dispose of every such application within such period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the invention is relevant for defence purpose or atomic energy, the Controller shall`
  line `not grant permit without the prior consent of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall not apply in relation to an invention for which an application for protection has`
  line `first been filed in a country outside India by a person resident outside India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (15910)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Liability for contravention of section 35 or section 39.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 22 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15910&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions`
  line `contained in Chapter XX, if in respect of an application for a patent any person contravenes any direction`
  line `as to secrecy given by the Controller under section 35 ^1[or makes or causes to be made an application for`
  line `grant of a patent outside India in contravention of section 39], or the application for patent under this Act`
  line `shall be deemed to have been abandoned and the patent granted, if any, shall be liable to be revoked under`
  line `section 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (15911)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Finality of orders of Controller and Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15911&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `All orders of the Controller`
  line `giving directions as to secrecy as well as all orders of the Central Government under this Chapter shall be`
  line `final and shall not be called in question in any court on any ground whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (15912)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Savings respecting disclosure to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15912&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be held to prevent the`
  line `disclosure by the Controller of information concerning an application for a patent or a specification filed`
  line `in pursuance thereof to the Central Government for the purpose of the application or specification being`
  line `examined for considering whether an order under this Chapter should be made or whether an order so`
  line `made should be revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (15913)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Grant of patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15913&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1,^2[43. Grant of patents.--(1) Where an application for a patent has been found to be in order for grant`
  line `of the patent and either--`
  line
  line `(a) the application has not been refused by the Controller by virtue of any power vested in him by`
  line `this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has not been found to be in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `the patent shall be granted as expeditiously as possible to the applicant or, in the case of a joint`
  line `application, to the applicants jointly, with the seal of the patent office and the date on which the patent is`
  line `granted shall be entered in the register.`
  line
  line `(2) On the grant of patent, the Controller shall publish the fact that the patent has been granted and`
  line `thereupon the application, specification and other documents related thereto shall be open for public`
  line inspection.]
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 32, for Chapter Heading (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for section 43 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (15914)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Amendment of patent granted to deceased applicant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for "sealed" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15914&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Where, at any time after a patent has`
  line `been ^1[granted] in pursuance of an application under this Act, the Controller is satisfied that the person to`
  line `whom the patent was granted had died, or, in the case of a body corporate, had ceased to exist, before the`
  line `patent was ^1[granted], the Controller may amend the patent by substituting for the name of that person the`
  line `name of the person to whom the patent ought to have been granted, and the patent shall have effect, and`
  line `shall be deemed always to have had effect, accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (15915)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Date of patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15915&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, every patent shall be`
  line `dated as of the date on which the application for patent was filed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The date of every patent shall be entered in the register.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no suit or other proceeding shall be`
  line `commenced or prosecuted in respect of an infringement committed before ^2[the date of publication of the`
  line application].
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 24, for sub-section (1) (we.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 35, for certain words (we.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (15916)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Form, extent and effect of patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15916&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every patent shall be in the prescribed form and shall`
  line `have effect throughout India.`
  line
  line `(2) A patent shall be granted for one invention only:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be competent for any person in a suit or other proceeding to take any`
  line `objection to a patent on the ground that it has been granted for more than one invention.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (15917)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Grant of patents to be subject to certain conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15917&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The grant of a patent under this Act shall`
  line `be subject to the condition that--`
  line
  line `(1) any machine, apparatus or other article in respect of which the patent is granted or any article`
  line `made by using a process in respect of which the patent is granted, may be imported or made by or on`
  line `behalf of the Government for the purpose merely of its own use;`
  line
  line `(2) any process in respect of which the patent is granted may be used by or on behalf of the`
  line `Government for the purpose merely of its own use;`
  line
  line `(3) any machine, apparatus or other article in respect of which the patent is granted or any article`
  line `made by the use of the process in respect of which the patent is granted, may be made or used, and any`
  line `process in respect of which the patent is granted may be used, by any person, for the purpose merely of`
  line `experiment or research including the imparting of instructions to pupils; and`
  line
  line `(4) in the case of a patent in respect of any medicine or drug, the medicine or drug may be imported`
  line `by the Government for the purpose merely of its own use or for distribution in any dispensary, hospital or`
  line `other medical institution maintained by or on behalf of the Government or any other dispensary, hospital`
  line `or other medical institution which the Central Government may, having regard to the public service that`
  line `such dispensary, hospital or medical institution renders, specify in this behalf by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (15918)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Rights of patentees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15918&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `^1[48. Rights of patentees.--Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act and the conditions`
  line `specified in section 47, a patent granted under this Act shall confer upon the patentee--`
  line
  line `(a) where the subject matter of the patent is a product, the exclusive right to prevent third parties,`
  line `who do not have his consent, from the act of making, using, offering for sale, selling or importing for`
  line `those purposes that product in India;`
  line
  line `(b) where the subject matter of the patent is a process, the exclusive right to prevent third parties,`
  line `who do not have his consent, from the act of using that process, and from the act of using, offering for`
  line `sale, selling or importing for those purposes the product obtained directly by that process in India.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 25, for section 48 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 15 of 2005, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (15919)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Patent rights not infringed when used on foreign vessels, etc., temporarily or accidentally in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15919&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a vessel or aircraft registered in a foreign country or a land vehicle owned by a person`
  line `ordinarily resident in such country comes into India (including the territorial waters thereof) temporarily`
  line `or accidentally only, the rights conferred by a patent for an invention shall not be deemed to be infringed`
  line `by the use of the invention--`
  line
  line `(a) in the body of the vessel or in the machinery, tackle, apparatus or other accessories thereof, so`
  line `far as the invention is used on board the vessel and for its actual needs only; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the construction or working of the aircraft or land vehicle or of the accessories thereof, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) This section shall not extend to vessels, aircraft or land vehicles owned by persons ordinarily`
  line `resident in a foreign country the laws of which do not confer corresponding rights with respect to the use`
  line `of inventions in vessels, aircraft or land vehicles owned by persons ordinarily resident in India while in`
  line `the ports or within the territorial waters of that foreign country or otherwise within the jurisdiction of its`
  line courts.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (15920)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Rights of co-owners of patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 26, for "make, use, exercise and sell the patented invention" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15920&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a patent is granted to two or more persons, each of`
  line `those persons shall, unless an agreement to the contrary is in force, be entitled to an equal undivided share`
  line `in the patent.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in this section and in section 51, where two or more persons`
  line `are registered as grantee or proprietor of a patent, then, unless an agreement to the contrary is in force,`
  line `each of those persons shall be entitled, by himself or his agents, to ^1[the rights conferred by section 48]`
  line `for his own benefit without accounting to the other person or persons.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in this section and in section 51 and to any agreement for the`
  line `time being in force, where two or more persons are registered as grantee or proprietor of a patent, then, a`
  line `licence under the patent shall not be granted and a share in the patent shall not be assigned by one of such`
  line `persons except with the consent of the other person or persons.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a patented article is sold by one of two or more persons registered as grantee or proprietor`
  line `of a patent, the purchaser and any person claiming through him shall be entitled to deal with the article in`
  line `the same manner as if the article had been sold by a sole patentee.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions contained in this section, the rules of law applicable to the ownership`
  line `and devolution of movable property generally shall apply in relation to patents; and nothing contained in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall affect the mutual rights or obligations of trustees or of the legal`
  line `representatives of a deceased person or their rights or obligations as such.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall affect the rights of the assignees of a partial interest in a patent`
  line `created before the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (15921)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of Controller to give directions to co-owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15921&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where two or more persons are`
  line `registered as grantee or proprietor of a patent, the Controller may, upon application made to him in the`
  line `prescribed manner by any of those persons, give such directions in accordance with the application as to`
  line `the sale or lease of the patent or any interest therein, the grant of licences under the patent, or the exercise`
  line `of any right under section 50 in relation thereto, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person registered as grantee or proprietor of a patent fails to execute any instrument or to do`
  line `any other thing required for the carrying out of any direction given under this section within fourteen days`
  line `after being requested in writing so to do by any of the other persons so registered, the Controller may,`
  line `upon application made to him in the prescribed manner by any such other person, give directions`
  line `empowering any person to execute that instrument or to do that thing in the name and on behalf of the`
  line `person in default.`
  line
  line `(3) Before giving any directions in pursuance of an application under this section, the Controller shall`
  line `give an opportunity to be heard--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an application under sub-section (1), to the other person or persons registered as`
  line `grantee or proprietor of the patent;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an application under sub-section (2), to the person in default.`
  line
  line `(4) No direction shall be given under this section so as to affect the mutual rights or obligation of`
  line `trustees or of the legal representatives of a deceased person or of their rights or obligations as such, or`
  line `which is inconsistent with the terms of any agreement between persons registered as grantee or proprietor`
  line `of the patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (15922)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Grant of patent to true and first inventions where it has been obtained by another in fraud of him.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15922&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Where the patent has been revoked under section 64] on the ground that the patent was`
  line `obtained wrongfully and in contravention of the rights of the petitioner or any person under or through`
  line `whom he claims, or, where in a petition for revocation, the ^2] ^3**** court], instead of`
  line `revoking the patent, directs the complete specification to be amended by the exclusion of a claim or`
  line `claims in consequence of a finding that the invention covered by such claim or claims had been obtained`
  line `from the petitioner, the ^2[ ^3**** court] may, by order passed in the same proceeding, permit`
  line `the grant to the petitioner of the whole or such part of the invention which the ^2[ ^3*** court]`
  line `finds has been wrongfully obtained by the patentee, in lieu of the patent so revoked or is excluded by`
  line amendment.
  line
  line `(2) Where any such order is passed, the Controller shall, on request by the petitioner made in the`
  line `prescribed manner grant to him:--`
  line
  line `(i) in cases where the ^2[ ^3*** court] permits the whole of the patent to be granted, a`
  line `new patent bearing the same date and number as the patent revoked;`
  line
  line `(ii) in cases where the ^2[ ^3 court] permits a part only of the patent to be granted,`
  line `a new patent for such part bearing the same date as the patent revoked and numbered in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Controller may, as a condition of such grant, require the petitioner to file a new and`
  line `complete specification to the satisfaction of the Controller describing and claiming that part of the`
  line `invention for which the patent is to be granted.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit shall be brought for any infringement of a patent granted under this section committed`
  line `before the actual date on which such patent was granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 37, for Where a patent has been revoked (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for court (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The word “Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (15923)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title `Term of patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15923&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the term of every patent granted,`
  line `after the commencement of the Patents (Amendment) Act, 2002, and the term of every patent which has`
  line `not expired and has not ceased to have effect, on the date of such commencement, under this Act, shall be`
  line `twenty years from the date of filing of the application for the patent.]`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the term of patent in case of International`
  line `applications filed under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India, shall be twenty years from the`
  line `international filing date accorded under the Patent Cooperation Treaty.]`
  line
  line `(2) A patent shall cease to have effect notwithstanding anything therein or in this Act on the`
  line `expiration of the period prescribed for the payment of any renewal fee, if that fee is not paid within the`
  line `prescribed period ^3[or within such extended period as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, on cessation of`
  line `the patent right due to non-payment of renewal fee or on the expiry of the term of patent, the subject`
  line `matter covered by the said patent shall not be entitled to any protection.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 27, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. The Explanation ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for "or within that period as extended under this section"(w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 27 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (15924)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 56
  title `Patents of addition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15924&sectionno=54&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in this section, where an`
  line `application is made for a patent in respect of any improvement in or modification of an invention`
  line `described or disclosed in the complete specification filed therefor (in this Act referred to as the "main`
  line `invention") and the applicant also applies or has applied for a patent for that invention or is the patentee in`
  line `respect thereof, the Controller may, if the applicant so requests, grant the patent for the improvement or`
  line `modification as a patent of addition.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in this section, where an invention, being an improvement in`
  line `or modification of another invention, is the subject of an independent patent and the patentee in respect of`
  line `that patent is also the patentee in respect of the patent for the main invention, the Controller may, if the`
  line `patentee so requests, by order, revoke the patent for the improvement or modification and grant to the`
  line `patentee a patent of addition in respect thereof, bearing the same date as the date of the patent so revoked.`
  line
  line `(3) A patent shall not be granted as a patent of addition unless the date of filing of the ^1[application]`
  line `was the same as or later than the date of filing of the ^1[application] in respect of the main invention.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) A patent of addition shallnot be granted before grant of the patent for the main invention].`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 39, for "complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (15925)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Term of patents of addition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15925&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1)A patent of addition shall be granted for a term equal to that of`
  line `the patent for the main invention, or so much thereof as has not expired, and shall remain in force during`
  line `that term or until the previous cesser of the patent for the main invention and no longer:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the patent for the main invention is revoked under this Act, the court, or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Controller, on request made to him by the patentee in the prescribed manner, may order that`
  line `the patent of addition shall become an independent patent for the remainder of the term for the patent for`
  line `the main invention and thereupon the patent shall continue in force as an independent patent accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) No renewal fees shall be payable in respect of a patent of addition, but, if any such patent`
  line `becomes an independent patent under sub-section (1), the same fees shall thereafter be payable, upon the`
  line `same dates, as if the patent had been originally granted as an independent patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (15926)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 58
  title `Validity of patents of addition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15926&sectionno=56&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `116. Appellate Board. Oi@Omitted by the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 201), s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-`
  line `2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (15927)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 59
  title `Amendment of application and specification before Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15927&sectionno=57&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1)Subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 59, the Controller may, upon application made under this section in the prescribed manner by`
  line `an applicant for a patent or by a patentee, allow the application for the patent or the complete`
  line `specification ^1[or any document relating thereto] to be amended subject to such conditions, if any, as the`
  line `Controller thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Controller shall not pass any order allowing or refusing an application to amend an`
  line `application for a patent or a specification ^1[or any document relating thereto] under this section while any`
  line `suit before a court for the infringement of the patent or any proceeding before the High Court for the`
  line `revocation of the patent is pending, whether the suit or proceeding commenced before or after the filing`
  line `of the application to amend.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for leave to amend an application for a patent ^2[or a complete specification or`
  line `any document relating thereto] under this section shall state the nature of the proposed amendment, and`
  line `shall give full particulars of the reasons for which the application is made.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Any application for leave to amend an application for a patent or a complete specification or a`
  line `document related thereto under this section made after the grant of patent and the nature of the proposed`
  line `amendment may be published.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is ^4[published] under sub-section (3), any person interested may, within the`
  line `prescribed period after the ^5[publication] thereof, give notice to the Controller of opposition thereto; and`
  line `where such a notice is given within the period aforesaid, the Controller shall notify the person by whom`
  line `the application under this section is made and shall give to that person and to the opponent an opportunity`
  line `to be heard before he decides the case.`
  line
  line `(5) An amendment under this section of a complete specification may be, or include, an amendment`
  line `of the priority date of a claim.`
  line
  line `^6[(6) The provisions of this section shall be without prejudice to the right of an applicant for a patent`
  line `to amend his specification or any other document related thereto to comply with the directions of the`
  line `Controller issued before the grant of a patent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 28 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for "or a specification" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 40, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for "advertised" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for "advertisement" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for sub-section (6) (w.e.f 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (15928)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 60
  title `Amendment of specification before Appellate Board or High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for section 58 (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15928&sectionno=58&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `^1[58. Amendment of specification before Appellate Board or High Court.—--(1) In any proceeding`
  line `before the Appellate Board or the High Court for the revocation of a patent, the Appellate Board or the`
  line `High Court, as the case may be, may, subject to the provisions contained in section 59, allow the patentee`
  line `to amend his complete specification in such manner and subject to such terms as to costs, advertisement`
  line `or otherwise, as the Appellate Board or the High Court may think fit, and if in any proceedings for`
  line `revocation the Appellate Board or the High Court decides that the patent is invalid, it may allow the`
  line `specification to be amended under this section instead of revoking the patent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application for an order under this section is made to the Appellate Board or the High`
  line `Court, the applicant shall give notice of the application to the Controller, and the Controller shall been`
  line `titled to appear and be heard, and shall appear if so directed by the Appellate Board or the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of all orders of the Appellate Board or the High Court allowing the patentee to amend the`
  line `specification shall be transmitted by the Appellate Board or the High Court to the Controller who shall,`
  line `on receipt thereof, cause an entry thereof and reference thereto to be made in the register.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (15929)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 61
  title `Supplementary provisions as to amendment of application or specification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15929&sectionno=59&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) No`
  line `amendment of an application for a patent or a complete specification or any document relating thereto`
  line `shall be made except by way of disclaimer, correction or explanation, and no amendment thereof shall be`
  line `allowed, except for the purpose of incorporation of actual fact, and no amendment of a complete`
  line `specification shall be allowed, the effect of which would be that the specification as amended would`
  line `claim or describe matter not in substance disclosed or shown in the specification before the amendment,`
  line `or that any claim of the specification as amended would not fall wholly within the scope of a claim of the`
  line `specification before the amendment.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where after the date of grant of patent any amendment of the specification or any other`
  line `documents related thereto is allowed by the Controller or by ^3*** the High Court, as the`
  line `case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) the amendment shall for all purposes be deemed to form part of the specification along with`
  line `other documents related thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) the fact that the specification or any other documents related thereto has been amended shall`
  line `be published as expeditiously as possible; and`
  line
  line `(c) the right of the applicant or patentee to make amendment shall not be called in question except`
  line `on the ground of fraud].`
  line
  line `(3) In construing the specification as amended, reference may be made to the specification as`
  line `originally accepted.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 29, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 42, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The words “the Appellate Board or” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (15930)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Applications for restoration of lapsed patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15930&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a patent has ceased to have effect`
  line `by reason of failure to pay any renewal fee within the ^1[period prescribed under section 53 or within such`
  line `period as may be allowed under sub-section (4) of section 142], the patentee or his legal representative,`
  line `and where the patent was held by two or more persons jointly, then, with the leave of the Controller, one`
  line `or more of them without joining the others, may, within ^2[eighteen months] from the date on which the`
  line `patent ceased to have effect, make an application for the restoration of the patent.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) An application under this section shall contain a statement, verified in the prescribed manner,`
  line `fully setting out the circumstances which led to the failure to pay the prescribed fee, and the Controller`
  line `may require from the applicant such further evidence as he may think necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 43, for "prescribed period or within that period as extended under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 53" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 30, for "one year" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (15931)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 63
  title `Procedure for disposal of applications for restoration of lapsed patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 44, for "advertise the application" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15931&sectionno=61&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, after hearing`
  line `the applicant in cases where the applicant so desires or the Controller thinks fit, the Controller is prima`
  line facie
  line `satisfied that the failure to pay the renewal fee was unintentional and that there has been no undue`
  line `delay in the making of the application, he shall ^1[publish the application] in the prescribed manner; and`
  line `within the prescribed period any person interested may give notice to the Controller of opposition thereto`
  line `on either or both of the following grounds, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the failure to pay the renewal fee was not unintentional; or`
  line
  line `(b) that there has been undue delay in the making of the application.`
  line
  line `(2)If notice of opposition is given within the period aforesaid, the Controller shall notify the`
  line `applicant, and shall give to him and to the opponent an opportunity to be heard before he decides the case.`
  line
  line `(3) If no notice of opposition is given within the period aforesaid or if in the case of opposition, the`
  line `decision of the Controller is in favour of the applicant, the Controller shall, upon payment of any unpaid`
  line `renewal fee and such additional fee as may be prescribed, restore the patent and any patent of addition`
  line `specified in the application which has ceased to have effect on the cesser of that patent.`
  line
  line `(4) The Controller may, if he thinks fit as a condition of restoring the patent, require that an entry`
  line `shall be made in the register of any document or matter which, under the provisions of this Act, has to be`
  line `entered in the register but which has not been so entered.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (15932)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 64
  title `Rights of patentees of lapsed patents which have been restored.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15932&sectionno=62&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a patent is`
  line `restored, the rights of the patentee shall be subject to such provisions as may be prescribed and to such`
  line `other provisions as the Controller thinks fit to impose for the protection or compensation of persons who`
  line `may have begun to avail themselves of, or have taken definite steps by contract or otherwise to avail`
  line `themselves of, the patented invention between the date when the patent ceased to have effect and the date`
  line `of the ^1[publication] of the application for restoration of the patent under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other proceeding shall be commenced or prosecuted in respect of an infringement of a`
  line `patent committed between the date on which the patent ceased to have effect and the ^2[date of`
  line `publication] of the application for restoration of the patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for "advertisement" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for "date of the advertisement" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (15933)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 65
  title `Surrender of patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15933&sectionno=63&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1)A patentee may, at any time by giving notice in the prescribed`
  line `manner to the Controller, offer to surrender his patent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such an offer is made, the Controller shall ^1[publish] the offer in the prescribed manner,`
  line `and also notify every person other than the patentee whose name appears in the register as having an`
  line `interest in the patent.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person interested may, within the prescribed period after ^2[such publication] give notice to`
  line `the Controller of opposition to the surrender, and where any such notice is given the Controller shall`
  line `notify the patentee.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Controller is satisfied after hearing the patentee and any opponent, if desirous of being`
  line `heard, that the patent may properly be surrendered, he may accept the offer and, by order revoke the`
  line patent.
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 46, for "advertise" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for "such advertisement" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (15934)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 66
  title `Revocation of Power patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15934&sectionno=64&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in this Act, a patent`
  line `whether granted before or after the commencement of this Act, may,`
  line `^1[be revoked on a petition of any`
  line `person interested or of the Central Government by ^2*** on a counter-claim in a suit for`
  line `infringement of the patent by the High Court] on any of the following grounds, that is to say--`
  line
  line `(a) that the invention, so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification, was claimed in`
  line `a valid claim of earlier priority date contained in the complete specification of another patent granted`
  line `in India;`
  line
  line `(b) that the patent was granted on the application of a person not entitled under the provisions of`
  line `this Act to apply therefor:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) that the patent was obtained wrongfully in contravention of the rights of the petitioner or any`
  line `person under or through whom he claims;`
  line
  line `(d) that the subject of any claim of the complete specification is not an invention within the`
  line `meaning of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is not new,`
  line `having regard to what was publicly known or publicly used in India before the priority date of the`
  line `claim or to what was published in India or elsewhere in any of the documents referred to in section`
  line `13:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification is obvious or`
  line `does not involve any inventive step, having regard to what was publicly known or publicly used in`
  line `India or what was published in India or elsewhere before the priority date of the claim:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(g) that the invention, so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification, is not useful;`
  line
  line `(h) that the complete specification does not sufficiently and fairly describe the invention and the`
  line `method by which it is to be performed, that is to say, that the description of the method or the`
  line `instructions for the working of the invention as contained in the complete specification are not by`
  line `themselves sufficient to enable a person in India possessing average skill in, and average knowledge`
  line `of, the art to which the invention relates, to work the invention, or that it does not disclose the best`
  line `method of performing it which was known to the applicant for the patent and for which he was`
  line `entitled to claim, protection;`
  line
  line `(i) that the scope of any claim of the complete specification is not sufficiently and clearly defined`
  line `or that any claim of the complete specification is not fairly based on the matter disclosed in the`
  line specification;
  line
  line `(j) that the patent was obtained on a false suggestion or representation;`
  line
  line `(k) that the subject of any claim of the complete specification is not patentable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was secretly`
  line `used in India, otherwise than as mentioned in sub-section (3), before the priority date of the claim;`
  line
  line `(m) that the applicant for the patent has failed to disclose to the Controller the information`
  line `required by section 8 or has furnished information which in any material particular was false to his`
  line knowledge;
  line
  line `(n) that the applicant contravened any direction for secrecy passed under section 35 ^4[or made or`
  line `caused to be made an application for the grant of a patent outside India in contravention of section`
  line 39];
  line
  line `(o) that leave to amend the complete specification under section 57 or section 58 was obtained by`
  line fraud;
  line
  line `^4[(p) that the complete specification does not disclose or wrongly mentions the source or`
  line `geographical origin of biological material used for the invention;`
  line
  line `(q) that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was anticipated`
  line `having regard to the knowledge, oral or otherwise, available within any local or indigenous`
  line `community in India or elsewhere.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clauses (e) and (f) of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) no account shall be taken of ^5[personal document or secret trial or secret use]; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the patent is for a process or for a product as made by a process described or claimed`
  line `the importation into India of the product made abroad by that process shall constitute knowledge or`
  line `use in India of the invention on the date of the importation, except where such importation has been`
  line `for the purpose of reasonable trial or experiment only.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of clause (l) of sub-section (1), no account shall be taken of any use of the`
  line invention--
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of reasonable trial or experiment only; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the Government or by any person authorised by the Government or by a Government`
  line `undertaking, in consequence of the applicant for the patent or any person from whom he derives title`
  line `having communicated or disclosed the invention directly or indirectly to the Government or person`
  line `authorised as aforesaid or to the Government undertaking; or`
  line
  line `(c) by any other person, in consequence of the applicant for the patent or any person from whom`
  line `he derives title having communicated or disclosed the invention, and without the consent or`
  line `acquiescence of the applicant or of any person from whom he derives title.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), a patent may be revoked by the`
  line `High Court on the petition of the Central Government, if the High Court is satisfied that the patentee has`
  line `without reasonable cause failed to comply with the request of the Central Government to make, use or`
  line `exercise the patented invention for the purposes of Government within the meaning of section 99 upon`
  line `reasonable terms.`
  line
  line `(5) A notice of any petition for revocation of a patent under this section shall be served on all persons`
  line `appearing from the register to be proprietors of that patent or to have shares or interests therein and it`
  line `shall not be necessary to serve a notice on any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The words “by the Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 31 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 31 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for secret use (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (15935)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 67
  title `Revocation of patent or amendment of complete specification on directions from Government in cases relating to atomic energy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 48, for section 65 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15935&sectionno=65&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `^1[[65. Revocation of patent or amendment of complete specification on directions from`
  line `Government in cases relating to atomic energy.--(1)Where at any time after grant of a patent, the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that a patent is for an invention relating to atomic energy for which no`
  line `patent can be granted under sub-section (1) of section 20 of the Atomic Energy Act, 1962 (33 of 1962), it`
  line `may direct the Controller to revoke the patent, and thereupon the Controller, after giving notice, to the`
  line `patentee and every other person whose name has been entered in the register as having an interest in the`
  line `patent, and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, may revoke the patent.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceedings under sub-section (1), the Controller may allow the patentee to amend the`
  line `complete specification in such manner as he considers necessary instead of revoking the patent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (15936)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 68
  title `Revocation of patent in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15936&sectionno=66&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Government is of opinion that a`
  line `patent or the mode in which it is exercised is mischievous to the State or generally prejudicial to the`
  line `public, it may, after giving the patentee an opportunity to be heard, make a declaration to that effect in the`
  line `Official Gazette and thereupon the patent shall be deemed to be revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (15937)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 69
  title `Register of patents and particulars to be entered therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 32, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15937&sectionno=67&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be kept at the patent`
  line `office a register of patents, wherein shall be entered--`
  line
  line `(a) the names and addresses of grantees of patents;`
  line
  line `(b) notifications of assignments and of transmissions of patents, of licences under patents, and of`
  line `amendments, extensions, an revocations of patents; and`
  line
  line `(c) particulars of such other matters affecting the validity or proprietorship of patents as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) No notice of any trust, whether express, implied or constructive, shall be entered in the register,`
  line `and the Controller shall not be affected by any such notice.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the superintendence and direction of the Central Government, the register shall be kept`
  line `under the control and management of the Controller.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),it shall be lawful for the Controller to`
  line `keep the register of patents or any part thereof in computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form`
  line `subject to such safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), a copy of, or`
  line `extracts from, the register of patents, certified to be a true copy under the hand of the Controller or any`
  line `officer duly authorised by the Controller in this behalf shall, in all legal proceedings, be admissible in`
  line evidence.
  line
  line `(6) In the event the register is kept wholly or partly in computer floppies, diskettes or any other`
  line `electronic form,--`
  line
  line `(a)reference in this Act to an entry in the register shall be deemed to include reference to a record`
  line `of particulars kept in computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form and comprising the`
  line `register or part of the register;`
  line
  line `(b)references in this Act to particulars being registered or entered in the register shall be deemed`
  line `to include references to the keeping of record of those particulars comprising the register or part of`
  line `the register in computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form; and`
  line
  line `(c) references in this Act to the rectification of the register are to be read as including references`
  line `to the rectification of the record of particulars kept in computer floppies, diskettes or any other`
  line `electronic form and comprising the register or part of the register.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (15938)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 70
  title `Assignments, etc., not to be valid unless in writing and duly executed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 49, for section 68 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15938&sectionno=68&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `^1[68. Assignments, etc., not to be valid unless in writing and duly executed.--An assignment of a`
  line `patent or of a share in a patent, a mortgage, licence or the creation of any other interest in a patent shall`
  line `not be valid unless the same were in writing and the agreement between the parties concerned is reduced`
  line `to the form of a document embodying all the terms and conditions governing their rights and obligations`
  line `and duly executed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (15939)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 71
  title `Registration of assignments, transmissions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15939&sectionno=69&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person becomes entitled by`
  line `assignment, transmission or operation of law to a patent or to a share in a patent or becomes entitled as a`
  line `mortgagee, licensee or otherwise to any other interest in a patent, he shall apply in writing in the`
  line `prescribed manner to the Controller for the registration of his title or, as the case may be, of notice of his`
  line `interest in the register.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), an application for the registration of the`
  line `title of any person becoming entitled by assignment to a patent or a share in a patent or becoming entitled`
  line `by virtue of a mortgage, licence or other instrument to any other interest in a patent may be made in the`
  line `prescribed manner by the assignor, mortgagor, licensor or other party to that instrument, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made under this section for the registration of the title of any person the`
  line `Controller shall, upon proof of title to his satisfaction,--`
  line
  line `(a) where that person is entitled to a patent or a share in a patent, register him in the register as`
  line `proprietor or co-proprietor of the patent, and enter in the register particulars of the instrument or event`
  line `by which he derives title; or`
  line
  line `(b) where that person is entitled to any other interest in the patent, enter in the register notice of`
  line `his interest, with particulars of the instrument, if any, creating it:`
  line
  line `Provided that if there is any dispute between the parties whether the assignment, mortgage, licence,`
  line `transmission, operation of law or any other such transaction has validly vested in such person a title to the`
  line `patent or any share or interest therein, the Controller may refuse to take any action under clause (a) or, as`
  line `the case may be, under clause (b), until the rights of the parties have been determined by a competent`
  line court.
  line
  line `(4) There shall be supplied to the Controller in the prescribed manner for being filed in the patent`
  line `office copies of all agreements, licences and other documents affecting the title to any patent or any`
  line `licence thereunder authenticated in the prescribed manner and also such other documents as may be`
  line `prescribed relevant to the subject-matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a licence granted under a patent, the Controller shall, if so requested by`
  line `the patentee or licensee, take steps for securing that the terms of the licence are not disclosed to any`
  line `person except under the order of a court.`
  line
  line `(5) Except for the purposes of an application under sub-section (1) or of an application to rectify the`
  line `register, a document in respect of which no entry has been made in the register under sub-section (3) shall`
  line `not be admitted by the Controller or by any court as evidence of the title of any person to a patent or to a`
  line `share or interest therein unless the Controller or the court, for reasons to be recorded in writing, otherwise`
  line directs.
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (15940)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power of registered grantee or proprietor to deal with patent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15940&sectionno=70&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions`
  line `contained in this Act relating to co-ownership of patents and subject also to any rights vested in any other`
  line `person of which notice is entered in the register, the person or persons registered as grantee or proprietor`
  line `of a patent shall have power to assign, grant licences under, or otherwise deal with, the patent and to give`
  line `effectual receipts for any consideration for any such assignment, licence or dealing:`
  line
  line `Provided that any equities in respect of the patent may be enforced in like manner as in respect of any`
  line `other movable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (15941)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 73
  title `Rectification of register by Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15941&sectionno=71&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `71. Rectification of register`
  line `by ^1[Appellate Board].--(1) The ^1[Appellate Board] may, on the`
  line `application of any person aggrieved--`
  line
  line `(a) by the absence or omission from the register of any entry; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any entry made in the register without sufficient cause; or`
  line
  line `(c) by any entry wrongly remaining on the register; or`
  line
  line `(d) by any error or defect in any entry in the register,`
  line
  line `make such order for the making, variation or deletion, of any entry therein as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceeding under this section the ^1[Appellate Board] may decide any question that may be`
  line `necessary or expedient to decide in connection with the rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(3) Notice of any application to the ^1[Appellate Board] under this section shall be given in the`
  line `prescribed manner to the Controller who shall be entitled to appear and be heard on the application, and`
  line `shall appear if so directed by the ^2[Board].`
  line
  line `(4) Any order of the ^1[Appellate Board] under this section rectifying the register shall direct that`
  line `notice of the rectification shall be served upon the Controller in the prescribed manner who shall upon`
  line `receipt of such notice rectify the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 2, for "High Court" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Court" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (15942)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 74
  title `Register to be open for inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15942&sectionno=72&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in this Act and any`
  line `rules made thereunder, the register shall at all convenient times be open to inspection by the public; and`
  line `certified copies, sealed with the seal of the patent office, of any entry in the register shall be given to any`
  line `person requiring them on payment of the prescribed fee.`
  line
  line `(2) The register shall be prima facie evidence of any matters required or authorised by or under this`
  line `Act to be entered therein.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) If the record of particulars is kept in computer floppies or diskettes or in any other electronic`
  line `form, sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be deemed to have been complied with if the public is given access to`
  line `such computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form or printouts of such record of particulars`
  line `for inspection.]`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (15943)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 75
  title `Controller and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15943&sectionno=73&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller General of Patents, Designs and TradeMarks`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) of ^1[section 3 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999)],shall be the`
  line `Controller of Patents for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, the Central Government may appoint as many examiners and other`
  line `officers and with such designations as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the officers appointed under sub-section (2) shall discharge`
  line `under the superintendence and directions of the Controller such functions of the Controller under this Act`
  line `as he may, from time to time by general or special order in writing, authorise them to discharge.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (3), the Controller may, by`
  line `order in writing and for reasons to be recorded therein withdraw any matter pending before an officer`
  line `appointed under sub-section (2) and deal with such matter himself either de novo or from the stage it was`
  line `so withdrawn or transfer the same to another officer appointed under sub-section (2) who may, subject to`
  line `special directions in the order of transfer, proceed with the matter either de novo or from the stage it was`
  line `so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (15944)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 76
  title `Patent office and its branches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 50, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15944&sectionno=74&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, there shall be an office which`
  line `shall be known as the patent office.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the name of the`
  line `Patent Office.]`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the patent office shall be at such place as the Central Government may specify,`
  line `and for the purpose of facilitating, the registration of patents there may be established, at such other`
  line `places as the Central Government may think fit, branch offices of the patent office.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be a seal of the patent office.`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (15945)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 77
  title `Restriction on employees of patent office as to right or interest in patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15945&sectionno=75&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `All officers and`
  line `employees of the patents office shall be incapable, during the period for which they hold their`
  line `appointments, to acquire or take, directly or indirectly, except by inheritance or bequest, any right or`
  line `interest in any patent issued by that office.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (15946)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 78
  title `Officers and employees not to furnish information, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15946&sectionno=76&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `An officer or employee in the patent`
  line `office shall not, except when required or authorised by this Act or under a direction in writing of the`
  line `^1[Central Government ^2*** ] or the Controller or by order of a court,--`
  line
  line `(a) furnish information on a matter which is being, or has been, or dealt with under this Act ^3***;`
  line
  line `(b) prepare or assist in the preparation of a document required or permitted by or under this Act`
  line `^3*** to be lodged in the patent office; or`
  line
  line `(c) conduct a search in the records of the patent office.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 36, for Central Government (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. The words “or Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words and figures or under the Indian Patents or Designs Act, 1911 (2 of 1911) omitted by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (15947)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 79
  title `Controller to have certain powers of a civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15947&sectionno=77&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1)Subject to any rules made in this behalf,`
  line `the Controller in any proceedings before him under this Act shall have the powers of a civil court while`
  line `trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure,1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) awarding costs;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing his own decision on application made within the prescribed time and in the`
  line `prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside an order passed ex parte on application made within the prescribed time and in`
  line `the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order for costs awarded by the Controller in exercise of the powers conferred upon him under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be executable as a decree of a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (15948)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 80
  title `Power of Controller to correct clerical errors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15948&sectionno=78&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1)Without prejudice to the provisions`
  line `contained in sections 57 and 59 as regards amendment of applications for patents or complete`
  line `specifications ^1[or other documents relating thereto] and subject to the provisions of section 44, the`
  line `Controller may, in accordance with the provisions of this section, correct any clerical error in any patent`
  line `or in any specification or other document filed in pursuance of such application or in any application for a`
  line `patent or any clerical error in any matter which is entered in the register.`
  line
  line `(2) A correction may be made in pursuance of this section either upon a request in writing made by`
  line `any person interested and accompanied by the prescribed fee, or without such a request.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Controller proposes to make any such correction as aforesaid otherwise than in`
  line `pursuance of a request made under this section, he shall give notice of the proposal to the patentee or the`
  line `applicant for the patent, as the case may be, and to any other person who appears to him to be concerned,`
  line `and shall give them an opportunity to be heard before making the correction.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a request is made under this section for the correction of any error in a patent or`
  line `application for a patent or any document filed in pursuance of such an application, and it appears to the`
  line `Controller that the correction would materially alter the meaning or scope of the document to which the`
  line `request relates and ought not to be made without notice to persons affected thereby, he shall require`
  line `notice of the nature of the proposed correction to be ^2[published] in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(5) Within the prescribed time after any ^3[such publication] as aforesaid any person interested may`
  line `give notice to the Controller of opposition to the request, and, where such notice of opposition is given,`
  line `the Controller shall give notice thereof to the person by whom the request was made, and shall give to`
  line `him and to the opponent an opportunity to be heard before he decides the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 51, for "advertised" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 51, ibid., for "such advertisement" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (15949)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 81
  title `Evidence how to be given and powers of Controller in respect thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15949&sectionno=79&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules`
  line `made in this behalf, in any proceeding under this Act before the Controller, evidence shall be given by`
  line `affidavit in the absence of directions by the Controller to the contrary, but in any case in which the`
  line `Controller thinks it right so to do, he may take oral evidence in lieu of, or in addition to, evidence by`
  line `affidavit, or may allow any party to be cross-examined on the contents of his affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (15950)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 82
  title `Exercise of discretionary powers by Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 38 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15950&sectionno=80&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any provision contained`
  line `in this Act requiring the Controller to hear any party to the proceedings thereunder or to give any such`
  line `party an opportunity to be heard, the Controller shall give to any applicant for a patent, or for amendment`
  line `of a specification (if within the prescribed time the applicant so requires) an opportunity to be heard`
  line `before exercising adversely to the applicant any discretion vested in the Controller by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the party desiring a hearing makes the request for such hearing to the Controller at`
  line `least ten days in advance of the expiry of the time-limit specified in respect of the proceeding.]`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (15951)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 83
  title `Disposal by Controller of applications for extension of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15951&sectionno=81&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Where under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder the Controller may extend the time for doing any act, nothing in this`
  line `Act shall be deemed to require him to give notice to or hear the party interested in opposing the extension,`
  line `nor shall any appeal lie from any order of the Controller granting such extension.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (15952)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 84
  title `Definition of "patented articles" and "patentee".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for Chapter XVI (sections 82 to 98) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15952&sectionno=82&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `^1[82. Definition of "patented articles" and "patentee".--In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise`
  line requires,--
  line
  line `(a) "patented article" includes any article made by a patented process; and`
  line
  line `(b) "patentee" includes an exclusive licensee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (15953)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 85
  title `General principles applicable to working of patented inventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15953&sectionno=83&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the`
  line `other provisions contained in this Act, in exercising the powers conferred by this Chapter, regard shall be`
  line `had to the following general considerations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that patents are granted to encourage inventions and to secure that the inventions are worked`
  line `in India on a commercial scale and to the fullest extent that is reasonably practicable without undue`
  line delay;
  line
  line `(b) that they are not granted merely to enable patentees to enjoy a monopoly for the importation`
  line `of the patented article;`
  line
  line `(c) that the protection and enforcement of patent rights contribute to the promotion of`
  line `technological innovation and to the transfer and dissemination of technology, to the mutual advantage`
  line `of producers and users of technological knowledge and in a manner conducive to social and economic`
  line `welfare, and to a balance of rights and obligations;`
  line
  line `(d) that patents granted do not impede protection of public health and nutrition and should act as`
  line `instrument to promote public interest specially in sectors of vital importance for socio-economic and`
  line `technological development of India;`
  line
  line `(e) that patents granted do not in any way prohibit Central Government in taking measures to`
  line `protect public health;`
  line
  line `(f) that the patent right is not abused by the patentee or person deriving title or interest on patent`
  line `from the patentee, and the patentee or a person deriving title or interest on patent from the patentee`
  line `does not resort to practices which unreasonably restrain trade or adversely affect the international`
  line `transfer of technology; and`
  line
  line `(g) that patents are granted to make the benefit of the patented invention available at reasonably`
  line `affordable prices to the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (15954)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 86
  title `Compulsory licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15954&sectionno=84&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after the expiration of three years from the date of`
  line `the ^1[grant] of patent, any person interested may make an application to the Controller for grant of`
  line `compulsory licence on patent on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the reasonable requirements of the public with respect to the patented invention have not`
  line `been satisfied, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the patented invention is not available to the public at a reasonably affordable price, or`
  line
  line `(c) that the patented invention is not worked in the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under this section may be made by any person notwithstanding that he is already`
  line `the holder of a licence under the patent and no person shall be estopped from alleging that the reasonable`
  line `requirements of the public with respect to the patented invention are not satisfied or that the patented`
  line `invention is not worked in the territory of India or that the patented invention is not available to the public`
  line `at a reasonably affordable price by reason of any admission made by him, whether in such a licence or`
  line `otherwise or by reason of his having accepted such a licence.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (1) shall contain a statement setting out the nature of the`
  line `applicants interest together with such particulars as may be prescribed and the facts upon which the`
  line `application is based.`
  line
  line `(4) The Controller, if satisfied that the reasonable requirements of the public with respect to the`
  line `patented invention have not been satisfied or that the patented invention is not worked in the territory of`
  line `India or that the patented invention is not available to the public at a reasonably affordable price, may`
  line `grant a licence upon such terms as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Controller directs the patentee to grant a licence he may, as incidental thereto, exercise`
  line `the powers set out in section 88.`
  line
  line `(6) In considering the application filed under this section, the Controller shall take into account,--`
  line
  line `(i) the nature of the invention, the time which has elapsed since the sealing of the patent and the`
  line `measures already taken by the patentee or any licensee to make full use of the invention;`
  line
  line `(ii) the ability of the applicant to work the invention to the public advantage;`
  line
  line `(iii) the capacity of the applicant to undertake the risk in providing capital and working the`
  line `invention, if the application were granted;`
  line
  line `(iv) as to whether the applicant has made efforts to obtain a licence from the patentee on`
  line `reasonable terms and conditions and such efforts have not been successful within a reasonable period`
  line `as the Controller may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that this clause shall not be applicable in case of national emergency or other`
  line `circumstances of extreme urgency or in case of public non-commercial use or on establishment of a`
  line `ground of anti-competitive practices adopted by the patentee,`
  line
  line `but shall not be required to take into account matters subsequent to the making of the application.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of clause (iv), "reasonable period" shall be construed as a period`
  line `not ordinarily exceeding a period of six months.]`
  line
  line `(7) For the purposes of this Chapter, the reasonable requirements of the public shall be deemed not to`
  line `have been satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) if, by reason of the refusal of the patentee to grant a licence or licences on reasonable`
  line terms,--
  line
  line `(i) an existing trade or industry or the development thereof or the establishment of any new`
  line `trade or industry in India or the trade or industry of any person or class of persons trading or`
  line `manufacturing in India is prejudiced; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the demand for the patented article has not been met to an adequate extent or on`
  line `reasonable terms; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a market for export of the patented article manufactured in India is not being supplied or`
  line `developed; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the establishment or development of commercial activities in India is prejudiced; or`
  line
  line `(b) if, by reason of conditions imposed by the patentee upon the grant of licences under the patent`
  line `or upon the purchase, hire or use of the patented article or process, the manufacture, use or sale of`
  line `materials not protected by the patent, or the establishment or development of any trade or industry in`
  line `India, is prejudiced; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the patentee imposes a condition upon the grant of licences under the patent to provide`
  line `exclusive grant back, prevention to challenges to the validity of patent or coercive package licensing,`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) if the patented invention is not being worked in the territory of India on a commercial scale to`
  line `an adequate extent or is not being so worked to the fullest extent that is reasonably practicable, or`
  line
  line `(e) if the working of the patented invention in the territory of India on a commercial scale is being`
  line `prevented or hindered by the importation from abroad of the patented article by--`
  line
  line `(i) the patentee or persons claiming under him; or`
  line
  line `(ii) persons directly or indirectly purchasing from him; or`
  line
  line `(iii) other persons against whom the patentee is not taking or has not taken proceedings for`
  line infringement.
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 52, for "sealing" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. The Explanation ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (15955)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 87
  title `Revocation of patents by the Controller for non-working.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15955&sectionno=85&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in respect of a patent, a`
  line `compulsory licence has been granted, the Central Government or any person interested may, after the`
  line `expiration of two years from the date of the order granting the first compulsory licence, apply to the`
  line `Controller for an order revoking the patent on the ground that the patented invention has not been worked`
  line `in the territory of India or that reasonable requirements of the public with respect to the patented`
  line `invention has not been satisfied or that the patented invention is not available to the public at a reasonably`
  line `affordable price.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed, the`
  line `facts upon which the application is based, and, in the case of an application other than by the Central`
  line `Government, shall also set out the nature of the applicants interest.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller, if satisfied that the reasonable requirements of the public with respect to the`
  line `patented invention have not been satisfied or that patented invention have not been worked in the territory`
  line `of India or that the patented invention is not available to the public at a reasonably affordable price, may`
  line `make an order revoking the patent.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application under sub-section (1) shall ordinarily be decided within one year of its being`
  line `presented to the Controller.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (15956)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power of Controller to adjourn applications for compulsory licences, etc., in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15956&sectionno=86&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application under section 84 or section 85, as the case may be, is made on the grounds that`
  line `the patented invention has not been worked in the territory of India or on the ground mentioned in clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (7) of section 84 and the Controller is satisfied that the time which has elapsed since the`
  line `sealing of the patent has for any reason been insufficient to enable the invention to be worked on a`
  line `commercial scale to an adequate extent or to enable the invention to be so worked to the fullest extent that`
  line `is reasonably practicable, he may, by order, adjourn the further hearing of the application for such period`
  line `not exceeding twelve months in the aggregate as appears to him to be sufficient for the invention to be so`
  line `worked:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case where the patentee establishes that the reason why a patented invention`
  line `could not be worked as aforesaid before the date of the application was due to any State or Central Act or`
  line `any rule or regulation made thereunder or any order of the Government imposed otherwise than by way of`
  line `a condition for the working of the invention in the territory of India or for the disposal of the patented`
  line `articles or of the articles made by the process or by the use of the patented plant, machinery, or apparatus,`
  line `then, the period of adjournment ordered under this sub-section shall be reckoned from the date on which`
  line `the period during which the working of the invention was prevented by such Act, rule or regulation or`
  line `order of Government as computed from the date of the application, expires.`
  line
  line `(2) No adjournment under sub-section (1) shall be ordered unless the Controller is satisfied that the`
  line `patentee has taken with promptitude adequate or reasonable steps to start the working of the invention in`
  line `the territory of India on a commercial scale and to an adequate extent.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (15957)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 89
  title `Procedure for dealing with applications under sections 84 and 85.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 53, for "shall advertise the application in the Official Gazette" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15957&sectionno=87&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Controller`
  line `is satisfied, upon consideration of an application under section 84, or section 85, that a prima facie case`
  line `has been made out for the making of an order, he shall direct the applicant to serve copies of the`
  line `application upon the patentee and any other person appearing from the register to be interested in the`
  line `patent in respect of which the application is made, and ^1[shall publish the application in the official`
  line journal].
  line
  line `(2) The patentee or any other person desiring to oppose the application may within such time as may`
  line `be prescribed or within such further time as the Controller may on application (made either before or after`
  line `the expiration of the prescribed time) allow, give to the Controller notice of opposition.`
  line
  line `(3) Any such notice of opposition shall contain a statement setting out the grounds on which the`
  line `application is opposed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any such notice of opposition is duly given, the Controller shall notify the applicant, and`
  line `shall give to the applicant and the opponent an opportunity to be heard before deciding the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (15958)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 90
  title `Powers of Controller in granting compulsory licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15958&sectionno=88&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Controller is satisfied`
  line `on an application made under section 84 that the manufacture, use or sale of materials not protected by`
  line `the patent is prejudiced by reason of conditions imposed by the patentee upon the grant of licences under`
  line `the patent, or upon the purchase, hire or use of the patented article or process, he may, subject to the`
  line `provisions of that section, order the grant of licences under the patent to such customers of the applicant`
  line `as he thinks fit as well as to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application under section 84 is made by a person being the holder of a licence under the`
  line `patent, the Controller may, if he makes an order for the grant of a licence to the applicant, order the`
  line `existing licence to be cancelled, or may, if he thinks fit, instead of making an order for the grant of a`
  line `licence to the applicant, order the existing licence to be amended.`
  line
  line `(3) Where two or more patents are held by the same patentee and an applicant for a compulsory`
  line `licence establishes that the reasonable requirements of the public have not been satisfied with respect to`
  line `some only of the said patents, then, if the Controller is satisfied that the applicant cannot efficiently or`
  line `satisfactorily work the licence granted to him under those patents without infringing the other patents held`
  line `by the patentee and if those patents involve important technical advancement or considerable economic`
  line `significance in relation to the other patents, he may, by order, direct the grant of a licence in respect of the`
  line `other patents also to enable the licensee to work the patent or patents in regard to which a licence is`
  line `granted under section 84.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the terms and conditions of a licence have been settled by the Controller, the licensee may,`
  line `at any time after he has worked the invention on a commercial scale for a period of not less than twelve`
  line `months, make an application to the Controller for the revision of the terms and conditions on the ground`
  line `that the terms and conditions settled have proved to be more onerous than originally expected and that in`
  line `consequence thereof the licensee is unable to work the invention except at a loss:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall be entertained a second time.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (15959)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 91
  title `General purposes for granting compulsory licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15959&sectionno=89&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `The powers of the Controller upon an`
  line `application made under section 84 shall be exercised with a view to securing the following general`
  line `purposes, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) that patented inventions are worked on a commercial scale in the territory of India without`
  line `undue delay and to the fullest extent that is reasonably practicable;`
  line
  line `(b) that the interests of any person for the time being working or developing an invention in the`
  line `territory of India under the protection of a patent are not unfairly prejudiced.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (15960)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 92
  title `Terms and conditions of compulsory licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 54, for clause (vii) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15960&sectionno=90&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) In settling the terms and conditions of a`
  line `licence under section 84, the Controller shall endeavour to secure--`
  line
  line `(i) that the royalty and other remuneration, if any, reserved to the patentee or other person`
  line `beneficially entitled to the patent, is reasonable, having regard to the nature of the invention, the`
  line `expenditure incurred by the patentee in making the invention or in developing it and obtaining a`
  line `patent and keeping it in force and other relevant factors;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the patented invention is worked to the fullest extent by the person to whom the licence is`
  line `granted and with reasonable profit to him;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the patented articles are made available to the public at reasonably affordable prices;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the licence granted is a non-exclusive licence;`
  line
  line `(v) that the right of the licensee is non-assignable;`
  line
  line `(vi) that the licence is for the balance term of the patent unless a shorter term is consistent with`
  line `public interest;`
  line
  line `^1[(vii) that the licence is granted with a predominant purpose of supply in the Indian market and`
  line `that the licensee may also export the patented product, if need be in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-clause (iii) of clause (a) of sub-section (7) of section 84;`
  line
  line `(viii) that in the case of semi-conductor technology, the licence granted is to work the invention`
  line `for public non-commercial use;`
  line
  line `(ix) that in case the licence is granted to remedy a practice determined after judicial or`
  line `administrative process to be anti-competitive, the licensee shall be permitted to export the patented`
  line `product, if need be.]`
  line
  line `(2) No licence granted by the Controller shall authorise the licensee to import the patented article or`
  line `an article or substance made by a patented process from abroad where such importation would, but for`
  line `such authorisation, constitute an infringement of the rights of the patentee.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Central Government may, if in its`
  line `opinion it is necessary so to do, in the public interest, direct the Controller at any time to authorise any`
  line `licensee in respect of a patent to import the patented article or an article or substance made by a patented`
  line `process from abroad (subject to such conditions as it considers necessary to impose relating among other`
  line `matters to the royalty and other remuneration, if any, payable to the patentee, the quantum of import, the`
  line `sale price of the imported article and the period of importation), and thereupon the Controller shall give`
  line `effect to the directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (15961)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 93
  title `Licensing of related patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15961&sectionno=91&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the other provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, at any time after the sealing of a patent, any person who has the right to work any other`
  line `patented invention either as patentee or as licensee thereof, exclusive or otherwise, may apply to the`
  line `Controller for the grant of a licence of the first-mentioned patent on the ground that he is prevented or`
  line `hindered without such licence from working the other invention efficiently or to the best advantage`
  line possible.
  line
  line `(2) No order under sub-section (1) shall be made unless the Controller is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(i) that the applicant is able and willing to grant, or procure the grant to the patentee and his`
  line `licensees if they so desire, of a licence in respect of the other invention on reasonable terms; and`
  line
  line `(ii) that the other invention has made a substantial contribution to the establishment or`
  line `development of commercial or industrial activities in the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(3) When the Controller is satisfied that the conditions mentioned in sub-section (1) have been`
  line `established by the applicant, he may make an order on such terms as he thinks fit granting a licence under`
  line `the first-mentioned patent and a similar order under the other patent if so requested by the proprietor of`
  line `the first-mentioned patent or his licensee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the licence granted by the Controller shall be non-assignable except with the`
  line `assignment of the respective patents.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 87, 88, 89 and 90 shall apply to licences granted under this section as`
  line `they apply to licences granted under section 84.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (15962)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 94
  title `Special provision for compulsory licences on notifications by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15962&sectionno=92&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `the Central Government is satisfied, in respect of any patent in force in circumstances of national`
  line `emergency or in circumstances of extreme urgency or in case of public non-commercial use, that it is`
  line `necessary that compulsory licences should be granted at any time after the sealing thereof to work the`
  line `invention, it may make a declaration to that effect, by notification in the Official Gazette, and thereupon`
  line `the following provisions shall have effect, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Controller shall, on application made at any time after the notification by any person`
  line `interested, grant to the applicant a licence under the patent on such terms and conditions as he thinks`
  line fit;
  line
  line `(ii) in settling the terms and conditions of a licence granted under this section, the Controller shall`
  line `endeavour to secure that the articles manufactured under the patent shall be available to the public at`
  line `the lowest prices consistent with the patentees deriving a reasonable advantage from their patent`
  line rights.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 83, 87, 88, 89 and 90 shall apply in relation to the grant of licences`
  line `under this section as they apply in relation to the grant of licences under section 84.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where the Controller is satisfied on`
  line `consideration of the application referred to in clause (i) of sub-section (1) that it is necessary in--`
  line
  line `(i) a circumstance of national emergency; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a circumstance of extreme urgency; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a case of public non-commercial use,`
  line
  line `which may arise or is required, as the case may be, including public health crises, relating to Acquired`
  line `Immuno Deficiency Syndrome, human immunodeficiency virus, tuberculosis, malaria or other epidemics,`
  line `he shall not apply any procedure specified in section 87 in relation to that application for grant of licence`
  line `under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Controller shall, as soon as may be practicable, inform the patentee of the patent`
  line `relating to the application for such non-application of section 87.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92_a:
  sectionId (15963)
  sectionNo 92A
  orderNo 95
  title `Compulsory licence for export of patented pharmaceutical products in certain exceptional circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15963&sectionno=92A&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_92_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[92A. Compulsory licence for export of patented pharmaceutical products in certain`
  line `exceptional circumstances.--(1) Compulsory licence shall be available for manufacture and export of`
  line `patented pharmaceutical products to any country having insufficient or no manufacturing capacity in the`
  line `pharmaceutical sector for the concerned product to address public health problems, provided compulsory`
  line `licence has been granted by such country or such country has, by notification or otherwise, allowed`
  line `importation of the patented pharmaceutical products from India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall, on receipt of an application in the prescribed manner, grant a compulsory`
  line `licence solely for manufacture and export of the concerned pharmaceutical product to such country under`
  line `such terms and conditions as may be specified and published by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be without prejudice to the extent to which`
  line `pharmaceutical products produced under a compulsory licence can be exported under any other provision`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "pharmaceutical products" means any patented`
  line `product, or product manufactured through a patented process, of the pharmaceutical sector needed to`
  line `address public health problems and shall be inclusive of ingredients necessary for their manufacture and`
  line `diagnostic kits required for their use.]`
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (15964)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 96
  title `Order for licence to operate as a deed between parties concerned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15964&sectionno=93&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Any order for the grant of`
  line `a licence under this Chapter shall operate as if it were a deed granting a licence executed by the patentee`
  line `and all other necessary parties embodying the terms and conditions, if any, settled by the Controller.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (15965)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 97
  title `Termination of compulsory licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15965&sectionno=94&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) On an application made by the patentee or any other`
  line `person deriving title or interest in the patent, a compulsory licence granted under section 84 may be`
  line `terminated by the Controller, if and when the circumstances that gave rise to the grant thereof no longer`
  line `exist and such circumstances are unlikely to recur:`
  line
  line `Provided that the holder of the compulsory licence shall have the right to object to such termination.`
  line
  line `(2) While considering an application under sub-section (1), the Controller shall take into account that`
  line `the interest of the person who had previously been granted the licence is not unduly prejudiced..`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (15966)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 98
  title `Meaning of use of invention for purposes of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 40 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15966&sectionno=99&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1)For the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter, an invention is said to be used for the purposes of Government if it is made, used, exercised or`
  line `vended for the purposes of the Central Government, a State Government or a Government undertaking.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this Chapter shall apply in respect of any such importation making or using`
  line `of any machine, apparatus or other article or of any such using of any process or of any such importation,`
  line `using or distribution of any medicine or drug, as may be made by virtue of one or more of the conditions`
  line `specified in section 47.`
