obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (15967)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power of Central Government to use inventions for purposes of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15967&sectionno=100&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1)Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, at any time after an application for a patent has been filed`
  line `at the patent office or a patent has been granted, the Central Government and any person authorised in`
  line `writing by it, may use the invention for the purposes of Government in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an invention has, before the priority date of the relevant claim of the complete`
  line `specification, been duly recorded in a document, or tested or tried, by or on behalf of the Government or a`
  line `Government undertaking, otherwise than in consequence of the communication of the invention directly`
  line `or indirectly by the patentee or by a person from whom he derives title, any use of the invention by the`
  line `Central Government or any person authorised in writing by it for the purposes of Government may be`
  line `made free of any royalty or other remuneration to the patentee.`
  line
  line `(3) If and so far as the invention has not been so recorded or tried or tested as aforesaid, any use of the`
  line `invention made by the Central Government or any person authorised by it under sub-section (1), at any`
  line `time after ^1[grant of the patent] or in consequence of any such communication as aforesaid, shall be made`
  line `upon terms as may be agreed upon either before or after the use, between the Central Government or any`
  line `person authorised under sub-section (1) and the patentee, or, as may in default of agreement be`
  line `determined by the High Court on a reference under section 103:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that in case of any such use of any patent, the patentee shall be paid not more than`
  line `adequate remuneration in the circumstances of each case, taking into account the economic value of the`
  line `use of the patent.]`
  line
  line `(4) The authorisation by the Central Government in respect of an invention may be given under this`
  line `section, either before or after the patent is granted and either before or after the acts in respect of which`
  line `such authorisation is given or done, and may be given to any person, whether or not he is authorised`
  line `directly or indirectly by the applicant or the patentee to make, use, exercise or vend the invention or`
  line `import the machine, apparatus or other article or medicine or drug covered by such patent.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an invention has been used by or with the authority of the Central Government for the`
  line `purposes of Government under this section, then, ^3[except in case of national emergency or other`
  line `circumstances of extreme urgency or for non-commercial use], the Government shall notify the patentee`
  line `as soon as practicable of the fact and furnish him with such information as to the extent of the use of the`
  line `invention as he may, from time to time, reasonable require; and where the invention has been used for the`
  line `purposes of a Government undertaking, the Central Government may call for such information as may be`
  line `necessary for this purpose from such undertaking.`
  line
  line `(6) The right to make, use, exercise and vend an invention for the purposes of Government under subsection`
  line `(1) shall include the ^4[right to sell, on non-commercial basis, the goods] which have been made in`
  line `exercise of that right, and a purchaser of goods so sold, and a person claiming through him, shall have the`
  line `power to deal with the goods as if the Central Government or the person authorised under sub-section (1)`
  line `were the patentee of the invention.`
  line
  line `(7) Where in respect of a patent which has been the subject of an authorisation under this section,`
  line `there is an exclusive licensee as is referred to in sub-section (3) of section 101, or where such patent has`
  line `been assigned to the patentee in consideration of royalties or other benefits determined by reference to the`
  line `use of the invention (including payments by way of minimum royalty), the notice directed to be given`
  line `under sub-section (5) shall also be given to such exclusive licensee or assignor as the case may be, and the`
  line `reference to the patentee in sub-section (3) shall be deemed to include a reference to such assignor or`
  line `exclusive licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 56, for "the acceptance of the complete specification in respect of the patent" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 41, for the proviso (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for "right to sell the goods" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (15968)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 104
  title `Rights of third parties in respect of use of invention for purposes of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15968&sectionno=101&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `relation to any use of a patented invention, or an invention in respect of which an application for a patent`
  line `is pending, made for the purposes of Government--`
  line
  line `(a) by the Central Government or any person authorised by the Central Government under`
  line `section 100; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the patentee or applicant for the patent to the order made by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `the provisions of any licence, assignment or agreement granted or made, ^1`
  line ***
  line `between the patentee or`
  line `applicant for the patent (or any person who derives title from him or from whom he derives title) and any`
  line `person other than the Central Government shall be of no effect so far as those provisions--`
  line
  line `(i) restrict or regulate the use for the purposes of Government of the invention, or of any model,`
  line `document or information relating thereto, or`
  line
  line `(ii) provide for the making of payments in respect of any use of the invention or of the model,`
  line `document or information relating thereto for the purposes of Government ^2***,`
  line
  line `and the reproduction or publication of any model or document in connection with the said use for the`
  line `purposes of Government shall not be deemed to be an infringement of any copyright subsisting in the`
  line `model or document.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the patent, or the right to apply for or obtain the patent, has been assigned to the patentee in`
  line `consideration of royalties or other benefits determined by reference to the use of the invention ^2***, then,`
  line `in relation to any use of the invention made for the purposes of Government by the patentee to the order`
  line `of the Central Government, sub-section (3) of section 100 shall have effect as if that use were made by`
  line `the virtue of an authority given under that section; and any rise of the invention for the purposes of`
  line `Government by virtue of sub-section (3) of that section shall have effect as if the reference to the patentee`
  line `included a reference to the assignor of the patent, and any sum payable by virtue of that sub-section shall`
  line `be divided between the patentee and the assignor in such proportion as may be agreed upon between them`
  line `or as may in default of agreement be determined by the High Court on a reference under section 103.`
  line
  line `(3) Where by virtue of sub-section (3) of section 100, payments are required to be made by the`
  line `Central Government or persons authorised under sub-section (2) of that section in respect of the use of an`
  line `invention for the purposes of Government and where in respect of such patent there is an exclusive`
  line `licensee authorised under his licence to use the invention for the purposes of Government, such sum shall`
  line `be shared by the patentee and such licensee in such proportions, if any, as may be agreed upon between`
  line `them or as may in default of agreement be determined by the High Court on a reference under section 103`
  line `to be just, having regard to any expenditure incurred by the licensee--`
  line
  line `(a) in developing the said invention; or`
  line
  line `(b) in making payments to the patentees other than royalties or other benefits determined by`
  line `reference to the use of the invention ^3*** in consideration of the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.The words ", whether before or after the commencement of this Act," omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 42 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2.The brackets and words "(including payments by way of minimum royalty)" omitted by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3.The words "including payments by way of minimum royalty" omitted by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (15969)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 105
  title `Acquisition of inventions and patents by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15969&sectionno=102&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, if satisfied that it is necessary that an invention which is the subject of an application`
  line `for a patent or a patent should be acquired from the applicant or the patentee for a public purpose, publish`
  line `a notification to that effect in the Official Gazette, and thereupon the invention or patent and all rights in`
  line `respect of the invention or patent shall, by force of this section, stand transferred to and be vested in the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notice of the acquisition shall be given to the applicant, and, where a patent has been granted, to`
  line `the patentee and other persons, if any, appearing in the register as having an interest in the patent.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall pay to the applicant, or, as the case may be, the patentee and other`
  line `persons appearing on the register as having an interest in the patent such compensation as may be agreed`
  line `upon between the Central Government and the applicant, or the patentee and other persons; or, as may, in`
  line `default of agreement, be determined by the High Court on a reference under section 103 to be just having`
  line `regard to the expenditure incurred in connection with the invention and, in the case of a patent, the term`
  line `thereof, the period during which and the manner in which it has already been worked (including the`
  line `profits made during such period by the patentee or by his licensee whether exclusive or otherwise) and`
  line `other relevant factors.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (15970)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 106
  title `Reference to High Court of disputes as to use for purposes of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15970&sectionno=103&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `dispute as to the exercise by the Central Government or a person authorised by it of the powers conferred`
  line `by section 100, or as to terms for the use of an invention for the purposes of Government thereunder or as`
  line `to the right of any person to receive any part of a payment made in pursuance of sub-section (3) of that`
  line `section or as to the amount of compensation payable for the acquisition of an invention or a patent under`
  line `section 102, may be referred to the High Court by either party to the dispute in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the rules of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceeding under this section to which the Central Government is a party, the Central`
  line `Government may,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the patentee is a party to the proceedings, petition by way of counter-claim for revocation of`
  line `the patent on any ground upon which a patent may be revoked under section 64; and`
  line
  line `(b) whether a patentee is or is not a party to the proceedings, put in issue the validity of the patent`
  line `without petitioning for its revocation.`
  line
  line `(3) If in such proceedings as aforesaid any question arises whether an invention has been recorded,`
  line `tested or tried as is mentioned in section 100, and the disclosure of any document regarding the invention,`
  line `or of any evidence of the test or trial thereof, would, in the opinion of the Central Government, be`
  line `prejudicial to the public interest, the disclosure may be made confidentially to the advocate of the other`
  line `party or to an independent expert mutually agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(4) In determining under this section any dispute between the Central Government and any person as`
  line `to terms for the use of an invention for the purposes of Government, the High Court shall have regard to`
  line `any benefit or compensation which that person or any person from whom he derive title, may have`
  line `received, or may be entitled to receive, directly or indirectly in respect of the use of the invention in`
  line `question for the purposes of Government.`
  line
  line `(5) In any proceedings under this section, the High Court may at any time order the whole`
  line `proceedings or any question or issue of fact arising therein to be referred to an official referee,`
  line `commissioner or an arbitrator on such terms as the High Court may direct, and references to the High`
  line `Court in the foregoing provisions of this section shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the invention claimed in a patent was made by a person who at the time it was made was in`
  line `the service of the Central Government or of a State Government or was an employee of a Government`
  line `undertaking and the subject-matter of the invention is certified by the relevant Government or the`
  line `principal officer of the Government undertaking to be connected with the work done in the course of the`
  line `normal duties of the Government servant or employee of the Government undertaking, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any dispute of the nature referred to in sub-section (1) relating to the invention shall be disposed of by the Central Government conformably to the provisions of`
  line `this section so far as may be applicable, but before doing so the Central Government shall give an`
  line `opportunity to the patentee and such other parties as it considers have an interest in the matter to be heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (15971)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 107
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15971&sectionno=104&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `No suit for a declaration under section 105 or for any relief under section 106 or`
  line `for infringement of a patent shall be instituted in any court inferior to a district court having jurisdiction to`
  line `try the suit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a counter-claim for revocation of the patent is made by the defendant, the suit,`
  line `along with the counter-claim, shall be transferred to the High Court for decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104_a:
  sectionId (15972)
  sectionNo 104A
  orderNo 108
  title `Burden of proof in case of suits concerning infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 43 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15972&sectionno=104A&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_104_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[104A. Burden of proof in case of suits concerning infringement.--(1) In any suit for`
  line `infringement of a patent, where the subject matter of patent is a process for obtaining a product, the court`
  line `may direct the defendant to prove that the process used by him to obtain the product, identical to the`
  line `product of the patented process, is different from the patented process if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the subject matter of the patent is a process for obtaining a new product; or`
  line
  line `(b) there is a substantial likelihood that the identical product is made by the process, and the`
  line `patentee or a person deriving title or interest in the patent from him, has been unable through`
  line `reasonable efforts to determine the process actually used:`
  line
  line `Provided that the patentee or a person deriving title or interest in the patent from him, first proves that`
  line `the product is identical to the product directly obtained by the patented process.`
  line
  line `(2) In considering whether a party has discharged the burden imposed upon him by sub-section (1),`
  line `the court shall not require him to disclose any manufacturing or commercial secrets, if it appears to the`
  line `court that it would be unreasonable to do so.]`
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (15973)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 109
  title `Power of court to make declaration as to non-infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 57, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15973&sectionno=105&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1)Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 34 of the Specific Relief Act, 1963 (47 of 1963), any person may institute a suit for a`
  line `declaration that the use by him of any process, or the making, use or sale of any article by him does not,`
  line `or would not, constitute an infringement of a claim of a patent against the patentee or the holder of an`
  line `exclusive licence under the patent, notwithstanding that no assertion to the contrary has been made by the`
  line `patentee or the licensee, if it is shown--`
  line
  line `(a) that the plaintiff has applied in writing to the patentee or exclusive licensee for a written`
  line `acknowledgment to the effect of the declaration claimed and has furnished him with full particulars in`
  line `writing of the process or article in question; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the patentee or licensee has refused or neglected to give such an acknowledgment.`
  line
  line `(2) The costs of all parties in a suit for a declaration brought by virtue of this section shall, unless for`
  line `special reasons the court thinks fit to order otherwise, be paid by the plaintiff.`
  line
  line `(3) The validity of a claim of the specification of a patent shall not be called in question in a suit for a`
  line `declaration brought by virtue of this section, and accordingly the making or refusal of such a declaration`
  line `in the case of a patent shall not be deemed to imply that the patent is valid or invalid.`
  line
  line `(4) A suit for a declaration may be brought by virtue of this section at any time ^1[after the publication`
  line `of grant of a patent], and references in this section to the patentee shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (15974)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power of court to grant relief in cases of groundless threats of infringement proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for existing (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15974&sectionno=106&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person (whether entitled to or interested in a patent or an application for a patent or not)`
  line `threatens any other person by circulars or advertisements or by communications, oral or in writing`
  line `addressed to that or any other person, with proceedings for infringement of a patent, any person aggrieved`
  line `thereby may bring a suit against him praying for the following reliefs, that is to say--`
  line
  line `(a) a declaration to the effect that the threats are unjustifiable;`
  line
  line `(b) an injunction against the continuance of the threats; and`
  line
  line `(c) such damages, if any, as he has sustained thereby.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless in such suit the defendant proves that the acts in respect of which the proceedings were`
  line `threatened constitute or, if done, would constitute, an infringement of a patent or of rights arising from the`
  line `publication of a complete specification in respect of a claim of the specification not shown by the plaintiff`
  line `to be invalid, the court may grant to the plaintiff all or any of the reliefs prayed for.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A mere notification of the ^1[existence] of a patent does not constitute a threat of`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (15975)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 111
  title `Defences, etc., in suit for infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15975&sectionno=107&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit for infringement of a patent, every`
  line `ground on which it may be revoked under section 64 shall be available as a ground for defence.`
  line
  line `(2) In any suit for infringement of a patent by the making, using or importation of any machine,`
  line `apparatus or other article or by the using of any process or by the importation, use or distribution of any`
  line `medicine or drug, it shall be a ground for defence that such making, using, importation or distribution is`
  line `in accordance with any one or more of the conditions specified in section 47.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107_a:
  sectionId (15976)
  sectionNo 107A
  orderNo 112
  title `Certain acts not to be considered as infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15976&sectionno=107A&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_107_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[107A. Certain acts not to be considered as infringement.--For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any act of making, constructing, ^2[using, selling or importing] a patented invention solely for`
  line `uses reasonably related to the development and submission of information required under any law for`
  line `the time being in force, in India, or in a country other than India, that regulates the manufacture,`
  line `construction, ^3[use, sale or import] of any product;`
  line
  line `(b) importation of patented products by any person from a person ^4[who is duly authorised under`
  line `the law to produce and sell or distribute the product],`
  line
  line `shall not be considered as an infringement of patent rights.]`
obj_root_law_sections_107_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 44 (w.e.f 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 58, for "using or selling" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for "use or sale" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for "who is duly authorised by the patentee to sell or distribute the product" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (15977)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 113
  title `Reliefs in suits for infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15977&sectionno=108&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The reliefs which a court may grant in any suit for`
  line `infringement include an injunction (subject to such terms, if any, as the court thinks fit) and, at the option`
  line `of the plaintiff, either damages or an account of profits.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The court may also order that the goods which are found to be infringing and materials and`
  line `implement, the predominant use of which is in the creation of infringing goods shall be seized, forfeited`
  line `or destroyed, as the court deems fit under the circumstances of the case without payment of any`
  line compensation.]
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 108 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 38 of 2002, s. 45 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 45, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (15978)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 114
  title `Right of exclusive licensee to take proceedings against infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15978&sectionno=109&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) The holder of an`
  line `exclusive licence shall have the like right as the patentee to institute a suit in respect of any infringement`
  line `of the patent committed after the date of the licence, and in awarding damages or an account of profits or`
  line `granting any other relief in any such suit the court shall take into consideration any loss suffered or likely`
  line `to be suffered by the exclusive licensee as such or, as the case may be, the profits earned by means of the`
  line `infringement so far as it constitutes an infringement of the rights of the exclusive licensee as such.`
  line
  line `(2) In any suit for infringement of a patent by the holder of an exclusive licence under sub-section (1),`
  line `the patentee shall, unless he has joined as a plaintiff in the suit, be added as a defendant, but a patentee so`
  line `added as defendant shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (15979)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 115
  title `Right of licensee under section 84 to take proceedings against infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15979&sectionno=110&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `Any person to`
  line `whom a licence has been granted under section 84 shall be entitled to call upon the patentee to take`
  line `proceedings to prevent any infringement of the patent, and, if the patentee refuses or neglects to do so`
  line `within two months after being so called upon, the licensee may institute proceedings for the infringement`
  line `in his own name as though he were the patentee, making the patentee a defendant; but a patentee so added`
  line `as defendant shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (15980)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 116
  title `Restriction on power of court to grant damages or account of profits for infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15980&sectionno=111&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1)In a suit for infringement of a patent, damages or an account of profits shall not be granted against the`
  line `defendant who proves that at the date of the infringement he was not aware and had no reasonable`
  line `grounds for believing that the patent existed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A person shall not be deemed to have been aware or to have had reasonable grounds`
  line `for believing that a patent exists by reason only of the application to an article of the word "patent",`
  line `"patented" or any word or words expressing or implying that a patent has been obtained for the article,`
  line `unless the number of the patent accompanies the word or words in question.`
  line
  line `(2) In any suit for infringement of a patent the court may, if it thinks fit, refuse to grant any damages`
  line `or an account of profits in respect of any infringement committed after a failure to pay any renewal fee`
  line `within the prescribed period and before any extension of that period.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an amendment of a specification by way of disclaimer, correction or explanation has been`
  line `allowed under this Act after the publication of the specification, no damages or account of profits shall be`
  line `granted in any proceedings in respect of the use of the invention before the date of the decision allowing`
  line `the amendment, unless the court is satisfied that the specification as originally published was framed in`
  line `good faith and with reasonable skill and knowledge.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall affect the power of the court to grant an injunction in any suit for`
  line `infringement of a patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (15981)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 117
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15981&sectionno=112&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `[Restriction on power of`
  line `court to grant injunction in certain cases.]--Omitted by the Patents`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2002 (38 of 2002), s. 46 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (15982)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 118
  title `Certificate of validity of specification and costs of subsequent suits for infringement thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15982&sectionno=113&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If in any proceedings before ^2*** a High Court for the revocation of a patent under section 64 and section 104, ^3*** the validity of any claim of a specification is contested and that claim is found by ^2*** the High Court to be valid, ^2*** the High Court may certify that the validity of that claim was contested in those proceedings and`
  line `was upheld.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such certificate has been granted, then, if in any subsequent suit before a court for`
  line `infringement of that claim of the patent or in any subsequent proceeding for revocation of the patent in so`
  line `far as it relates to that claim, the patentee or other person relying on the validity of the claim obtains a`
  line `final order or judgment in his favour, he shall be entitled to an order for the payment of his full costs,`
  line `charges and expenses of an incidental to any such suit or proceeding properly incurred so far as they`
  line `concern the claim in respect of which the certificate was granted, unless the court trying the suit or`
  line `proceeding otherwise directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that the costs as specified in this sub-section shall not be ordered when the party disputing`
  line `the validity of the claim satisfies the court that he was not aware of the grant of the certificate when he`
  line `raised the dispute and withdrew forthwith such defence when he became aware of such a certificate.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be construed as authorising the courts ^2*** hearing appeals from decrees or orders in suits for infringement or petitions for revocation, as the`
  line `case may be, to pass orders for costs on the scale referred to therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 59, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The words “the Appellate Board or” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words “as the case may be” omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 59, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (15983)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 119
  title `Relief for infringement of partially valid specification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15983&sectionno=114&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in proceedings for infringement`
  line `of a patent it is found that any claim of the specification, being a claim in respect of which infringement is`
  line `alleged, is valid, but that any other claim is invalid, the court may grant relief in respect of any valid claim`
  line `which is infringed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court shall not grant relief except by way of injunction save in the circumstances`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Where the plaintiff proves that the invalid claim was framed in good faith and with reasonable`
  line `skill and knowledge, the court shall grant relief in respect of any valid claim which is infringed subject to`
  line `the discretion of the court as to costs and as to the date from which damages or an account of profits`
  line `should be reckoned, and in exercising such discretion the court may take into consideration the conduct of`
  line `the parties in inserting such invalid claims in the specification or permitting them to remain there.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (15984)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 120
  title `Scientific advisers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15984&sectionno=115&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit for infringement or in any proceeding before a court under`
  line `this Act, the court may at any time, and whether or not an application has been made by any party for that`
  line `purpose, appoint an independent scientific adviser to assist the court or to inquire and report upon any`
  line `such question of fact or of opinion (not involving a question of interpretation of law) as it may formulate`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The remuneration of the scientific adviser shall be fixed by the court and shall include the costs of`
  line `making a report and a proper daily fee for any day on which the scientific adviser may be required to`
  line `attend before the court, and such remuneration shall be defrayed out of moneys provided by Parliament`
  line `by law for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (15985)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 121
  title `Appellate Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15985&sectionno=116&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `^1[116. Appellate Board.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Appellate Board established`
  line `under section 83 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999) shall be the Appellate Board for the purposes`
  line `of this Act and the said Appellate Board shall exercise the jurisdiction, power and authority conferred on`
  line `it by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Technical Member of the Appellate Board for the purposes of this Act shall have`
  line `the qualifications specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Technical Member for the purposes of this`
  line `Act unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) has, at least five years, held the post of Controller under this Act or has exercised the`
  line `functions of the Controller under this Act for at least five years; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been for at least ten years, functioned as a Registered Patent Agent and possesses a degree`
  line `in engineering or technology or a masters degree in science from any University established under`
  line `law for the time being in force or equivalent;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 47, for Chapter XIX (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (c) omitted by Act 15 of 2005, s. 60 (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
