obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (15995)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 131
  title `Contravention of Secrecy provisions relating to certain inventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 48 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15995&sectionno=118&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `If any person fails to`
  line `comply with any direction given under section 35 ^1[or makes or causes to be made an application for the`
  line `grant of a patent in contravention of section 39], he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (15996)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 132
  title `Falsification of entries in register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15996&sectionno=119&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `If any person makes, or causes to be made, a false`
  line `entry in any register kept under this Act, or a writing falsely purporting to be a copy of an entry in such a`
  line `register, or produces or tenders, or causes to be produced or tendered, in evidence any such writing`
  line `knowing the entry or writing to be false, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (15997)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 133
  title `Unauthorised claim of patent rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 64, for "ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15997&sectionno=120&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `If any person falsely represents that any article sold by`
  line `him is patented in India or is the subject of an application for a patent in India, he shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to ^1[one lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `Explanation l.--For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to represent--`
  line
  line `(a) that an article is patented in India if there is stamped, engraved or impressed on, or otherwise`
  line `applied to, the article the word "patent" or "patented" or some other word expressing or implying that`
  line `a patent for the article has been obtained in India;`
  line
  line `(b) that an article is the subject of an application for a patent in India, if there are stamped,`
  line `engraved or impressed on, or otherwise applied to, the article the words "patent applied for", "patent`
  line `pending", or some other words implying that an application for a patent for the article has been made`
  line `in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The use of words "patent", "patented", "patent applied for", "patent pending" or`
  line `other words expressing or implying that an article is patented or that a patent has been applied for shall be`
  line `deemed to refer to a patent in force in India, or to a pending application for a patent in India, as the case`
  line `may be unless there is an accompanying indication that the patent has been obtained or applied for in any`
  line `country outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (15998)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 134
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15998&sectionno=121&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `If any person uses on his place of business or any`
  line `document issued by him or otherwise the words "patent office" or any other words which would`
  line `reasonably lead to the belief that his place of business is, or is officially connected with, the patent office,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (15999)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 135
  title `Refusal or failure to supply information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for "twenty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=15999&sectionno=122&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person refuses or fails to furnish:--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Central Government any information which he is required to furnish under sub-section`
  line `(5) of section 100;`
  line
  line `(b) to the Controller any information or statement which he is required to furnish by or under`
  line `section 146,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ^1[ten lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(2) If any person, being required to furnish any such information as is referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `furnishes information or statement which is false, and which he either knows or has reason to believe to`
  line `be false or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (16000)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 136
  title `Practice by non-registered patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 66, for "ten thousand rupees in the case of a first offence and forty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16000&sectionno=123&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `If any person contravenes the provisions of section`
  line `129, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ^1[one lakh rupees in the case of a first offence`
  line `and five lakh rupees] in the case of a second or subsequent offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (16001)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 137
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16001&sectionno=124&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1)If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124_a:
  sectionId (93234)
  sectionNo 124A
  orderNo 138
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
