obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (16002)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 140
  title `Register of patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 52, for section 125 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16002&sectionno=125&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `^1[125. Register of patent agents.--(1) The Controller shall maintain a register to be called the`
  line `register of patent agents in which shall be entered the names, addresses and other relevant particulars, as`
  line `may be prescribed, of all persons qualified to have their names so entered under section 126.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Controller to keep`
  line `the register of patent agents in computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form subject to such`
  line `safeguards as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (16003)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 141
  title `Qualifications for registration as patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16003&sectionno=126&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be qualified to have his`
  line `name entered in the register of patent agents if he fulfils the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) he is a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(b) he has completed the age of 21 years;`
  line
  line `(c) he has obtained a ^1[degree in science, engineering or technology from any University`
  line `established under law for the time being in force] in the territory of India or possesses such other`
  line `equivalent qualifications as the Central Government may specify in this behalf, and, in addition,--`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(ii) has passed the qualifying examination prescribed for the purpose;^3[or]`
  line
  line `^3[(iii) has, for a total period of not less than ten years, functioned either as an examiner or`
  line `discharged the functions of the Controller under section 73 or both, but ceased to hold any such`
  line `capacity at the time of making the application for registration;]`
  line
  line `(d) he has paid such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a person who has been registered as a`
  line `patent agent before the commencement of ^5[the Patents (Amendment) Act, 2005 (15 of 2005)] shall be`
  line `entitled to continue to be, or when required to be re-registered, as a patent agent, on payment of the fee as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for "degree from any University" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-clause (i) omitted by Act 15 of 2005, s. 67 ( w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 53 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 53, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 67, for "the Patents (Amendment) Act, 2002 (38 of 2002)" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (16004)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 142
  title `Rights of patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16004&sectionno=127&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in this Act and in any rules made`
  line `thereunder, every patent agent whose name is`
  line `entered in the register shall be entitled:--`
  line
  line `(a) to practice before the Controller; and`
  line
  line `(b) to prepare all documents, transact all business and discharge such other functions as may be`
  line `prescribed in connection with any proceeding before the Controller under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (16005)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 143
  title `Subscription and verification of certain documents by patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16005&sectionno=128&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1*** all`
  line `applications and communications to the Controller under this Act may be signed by a patent agent`
  line `authorised in writing in this behalf by the person concerned.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, brackets and figure "Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (2) and to any rules made under this`
  line `Act," omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 54 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 54, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (16006)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 144
  title `Restrictions on practice as patent agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16006&sectionno=129&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, either alone or in partnerships with`
  line `any other person, shall practise, describe or hold himself out as a patent agent, or permit himself to be so`
  line `described or held out, unless he is registered as a patent agent or, as the case may be, unless he and all his`
  line `partners are so registered.`
  line
  line `(2) No company or other body corporate shall practise, describe itself or hold itself out as patent`
  line `agents or permit itself to be so described or held out.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, practise as a patent agent includes any of the`
  line `following acts, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) applying for or obtaining patents in India or elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(b) preparing specifications or other documents for the purposes of this Act or of the patent law of`
  line `any other country;`
  line
  line `(c) giving advice other than of a scientific or technical nature as to the validity of patents or their`
  line infringement.
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (16007)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 145
  title `Removal from register of patent agents and restoration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16007&sectionno=130&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Controller] may remove`
  line `the name of any person from the register when ^2[he] is satisfied, after giving that person a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard and after such further inquiry, if any, as ^2[he] thinks fit to make--`
  line
  line `(i) that his name has been entered in the register by error or on account of misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of material fact;`
  line
  line `(ii) that he has been convicted of any offence and sentenced to a term of imprisonment or has`
  line `been guilty of misconduct in his professional capacity which in the opinion of the ^1[Controller]`
  line `renders him unfit to be kept in the register.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Controller] may, on application and on sufficient cause being shown, restore to the register`
  line `the name of any person removed therefrom.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for "it" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (16008)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 146
  title `Power of Controller to refuse to deal with certain agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16008&sectionno=131&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in`
  line `this behalf, the Controller may refuse to recognise as agent in respect of any business under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) any individual whose name has been removed from, and not restored to, the register;`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has been convicted of an offence under section 123;`
  line
  line `(c) any person, not being registered as a patent agent, who in the opinion of the Controller is`
  line `engaged wholly or mainly in acting as agent in applying for patents in India or elsewhere in the name`
  line `or for the benefit of the person by whom he is employed;`
  line
  line `(d) any company or firm, if any person whom the Controller could refuse to recognise as agent in`
  line `respect of any business under this Act, is acting as a director or manager of the company or is a`
  line `partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall refuse to recognise as agent in respect of any business under this Act any`
  line `person who neither resides nor has a place of business in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (16009)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 147
  title `Savings in respect of other persons authorised to act as agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16009&sectionno=132&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter`
  line `shall be deemed to prohibit--`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant for a patent ^1*** from drafting any specification or appearing or acting before`
  line `the Controller; or`
  line
  line `(b) an advocate, not being a patent agent, from taking part in any ^2[hearing before the Controller`
  line `on behalf of a party who is taking part in any proceedings under this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or any person, not being a patent agent, who is duly authorised by the applicant" omitted by Act 38 of 2002,`
  line `s. 56 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (16010)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 148
  title `Convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 68, for section 133 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16010&sectionno=133&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `^1[133. Convention countries.--Any country, which is a signatory or party or a group of countries,`
  line `union of countries or inter-governmental organisations which are signatories or parties to an international,`
  line `regional or bi-lateral treaty, convention or arrangement to which India is also a signatory or party and`
  line `which affords to the applicants for patents in India or to citizens of India similar privileges as are granted`
  line `to their own citizens or citizens to their member countries in respect of the grant of patents and protection`
  line `of patent rights shall be a convention country or convention countries for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (16011)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 149
  title `Notification as to countries not providing for reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16011&sectionno=134&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Where any country specified by`
  line `the Central Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette does not accord to citizens of`
  line `India the same rights in respect of the grant of patents and the protection of patent rights as it accords to`
  line `its own nationals, no national of such country shall be entitled, either solely or jointly with any other`
  line person,--
  line
  line `(a) to apply for the grant of a patent or be registered as the proprietor of a patent;`
  line
  line `(b) to be registered as the assignee of the proprietor of a patent; or`
  line
  line `(c) to apply for a licence or hold any licence under a patent granted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (16012)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 150
  title `Convention applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16012&sectionno=135&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section 6,`
  line `where a person has made an application for a patent in respect of an invention in a convention country`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the "basic application"), and that person or the legal representative or assignee`
  line `of that person makes an application under this Act for a patent within twelve months after the date on`
  line `which the basic application was made, the priority date of a claim of the complete specification, being a`
  line `claim based on matter disclosed in the basic application, is the date of making of the basic application.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where applications have been made for similar protection in respect of an invention in`
  line `two or more convention countries, the period of twelve months referred to in this sub-section shall be`
  line `reckoned from the date on which the earlier or earliest of the said applications was made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where applications for protection have been made in one or more convention countries in respect`
  line `of two or more inventions which are cognate or of which one is a modification of another, a single`
  line `convention application may, subject to the provisions contained in section 10, be made in respect of those`
  line `inventions at any time within twelve months from the date of the earliest of the said applications for`
  line `protection:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee payable on the making of any such application shall be the same as if separate`
  line `applications have been made in respect of each of the said inventions, and the requirements of clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 136 shall, in the case of any such application, apply separately to the`
  line `applications for protection in respect of each of the said inventions.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) In case of an application filed under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India and`
  line `claiming priority from a previously filed application in India, the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2)`
  line `shall apply as if the previously filed application were the basic application:`
  line
  line `Provided that a request for examination under section 11B shall be made only for one of the`
  line `applications filed in India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (16013)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 151
  title `Special provisions relating to convention applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16013&sectionno=136&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every convention application`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) be accompanied by a complete specification; and`
  line
  line `(b) specify the date on which and the convention country in which the application for protection,`
  line `or as the case may be, the first of such applications was made; and`
  line
  line `(c) state that no application for protection in respect of the invention had been made in a`
  line `convention country before that date by the applicant or by any person from whom he derives title.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in section 10, a complete specification filed with a convention`
  line `application may include claims in respect of developments of, or additions to, the invention in respect of`
  line `which the application for protection was made in a convention country, being developments or additions`
  line `in respect of which the applicant would be entitled under the provisions of section 6 to make a separate`
  line `application for a patent.`
  line
  line `(3) A convention application shall not be post-dated under sub-section (1) of section 17 to a date later`
  line `than the date on which under the provisions of this Act the application could have been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (16014)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 152
  title `Multiple priorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16014&sectionno=137&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where two or more applications for patents in respect of inventions`
  line `have been made in one or more convention countries and those inventions are so related as to constitute`
  line `one invention, one application may be made by any or all of the persons referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 135 within twelve months from the date on which the earlier or earliest of those applications was`
  line `made, in respect of the inventions disclosed in the specifications which accompanied the basic`
  line applications.
  line
  line `(2) The priority date of a claim of the complete specification, being a claim based on matters`
  line `disclosed in one or more of the basic applications, is the date on which that matter was first so disclosed.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this Act, a matter shall be deemed to have been disclosed in a basic`
  line `application for protection in a convention country if it was claimed or disclosed (otherwise than by way of`
  line `disclaimer or acknowledgment of a prior art) in that application, or any documents submitted by the`
  line `applicant for protection in support of and at the same time as that application, but no account shall be`
  line `taken of any disclosure effected by any such document unless a copy of the document is filed at the patent`
  line `office with the convention application or within such period as may be prescribed after the filing of that`
  line application.
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (16015)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 153
  title `Supplementary provisions as to convention applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16015&sectionno=138&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)Where a convention`
  line `application is made in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, the applicant shall furnish, when`
  line `required by the Controller, in addition to the complete specification, copies of the specifications or`
  line `corresponding documents filed or deposited by the applicant in the patent office of the convention country`
  line `as referred to in section 133 verified to the satisfaction of the Controller, within the prescribed period`
  line `from the date of communication by the Controller.]`
  line
  line `(2) If any such specification or other document is in a foreign language, a translation into English of`
  line `the specification or document, verified by affidavit or otherwise to the satisfaction of the Controller, shall`
  line `be ^2[furnished when required by the controller].`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this Act, the date on which an application was made in a convention country is`
  line `such date as the Controller is satisfied by certificate of the official chief or head of the patent office of the`
  line `convention country or otherwise, is the date on which the application was made in that convention`
  line country.
  line
  line `^3[(4) An international application filed under the Patent Cooperation Treaty designating India shall`
  line `have effect of filing an application for patent under section 7, section 54 and section 135, as the case may`
  line `be, and the title, description, claim and abstract and drawings, if any, filed in the international application`
  line `shall be taken as complete specification for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The filing date of an application for patent and its complete specification processed by the patent`
  line `office as designated office shall be the international filing date accorded under the Patent Cooperation`
  line Treaty.
  line
  line `(6) Amendment, if any, proposed by the applicant for an international application designating India or`
  line `designating and electing India before international searching authority or preliminary made examination`
  line `authority shall, if the applicant so desires, be taken as an amendment made before the patent office.]`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 58, for "annexed to the specification or document" (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 58, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (16016)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 154
  title `Other provisions of Act to apply to convention applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16016&sectionno=139&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Chapter, all the provisions of this Act shall apply in relation to a convention application and a patent`
  line `granted in pursuance thereof as they apply in relation to an ordinary application and a patent granted in`
  line `pursuance thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (16017)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 155
  title `Avoidance of certain restrictive conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16017&sectionno=140&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1)It shall not be lawful to insert--`
  line
  line `(i) in any contract for or in relation to the sale or lease of a patented article or an article made by a`
  line `patented process; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in a licence to manufacture or use a patented article; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in a licence to work any process protected by a patent, a condition the effect of which may`
  line be--
  line
  line `(a) to require the purchaser, lessee, or licensee to acquire from the vendor, lessor, or licensor,`
  line `or his nominees, or to prohibit him from acquiring or to restrict in any manner or to any extent his`
  line `right to acquire from any person or to prohibit him from acquiring except from the vendor, lessor,`
  line `or licensor or his nominees, any article other than the patented article or an article other than that`
  line `made by the patented process; or`
  line
  line `(b) to prohibit the purchaser, lessee or licensee from using, or to restrict in any manner or to`
  line `any extent the right of the purchaser, lessee or licensee, to use an article other than the patented`
  line `article or an article other than that made by the patented process, which is not supplied by the`
  line `vendor, lessor or licensor or his nominee; or`
  line
  line `(c) to prohibit the purchaser, lessee or licensee from using or to restrict in any manner or to`
  line `any extent the right of the purchaser, lessee or licensee to use any process other than the patented`
  line `process; or`
  line
  line `^1[(d)to provide exclusive grant back, prevention to challenges to validity of patent and`
  line `coercive package licensing,]`
  line
  line `and any such condition shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) A condition of the nature referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall not cease to be a condition falling within that sub-section merely by reason of the fact that the`
  line `agreement containing it has been entered into separately, whether before or after the contract relating`
  line `to the sale, lease or licence of the patented article or process.`
  line
  line `(3) In proceedings against any person for the infringement of a patent, it shall be a defence to prove`
  line `that at the time of the infringement there was in force a contract relating to the patent and containing a`
  line `condition declared unlawful by this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply if the plaintiff is not a party to the contract and proves to`
  line `the satisfaction of the court that the restrictive condition was inserted in the contract without his`
  line `knowledge and consent, express or implied.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) affect a condition in a contract by which a person is prohibited from selling goods other than`
  line `those of a particular person;`
  line
  line `(b) validate a contract which, but for this section, would be invalid;`
  line
  line `(c) affect a condition in a contract for the lease of, or licence to use, a patented article, by which`
  line `the lessor or licensor reserves to himself or his nominee the right to supply such new parts of the`
  line `patented article as may be required or to put or keep it in repair.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 59, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 38 of 2002, s. 59 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (16018)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 156
  title `Determination of certain contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes `1. The words"whether made before or after the commencement of this Act," omitted by s. 60, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16018&sectionno=141&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1)Any contract for the sale or lease of a patented article`
  line `or for licence to manufacture, use or work a patented article or process, or relating to any such sale, lease`
  line `or licence^1*** may at any time after the patent or all the patents by which the article or process was`
  line `protected at the time of the making of the contract has or have ceased to be in force, and notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary in the contract or in any other contract, be determined by the purchaser, lessee, or`
  line `licensee, as the case may be, of the patent on giving three months notice in writing to the other party.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall be without prejudice to any right of determining a contract`
  line `exercisable apart from this section`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (16019)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 157
  title Fees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16019&sectionno=142&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1)There shall be paid in respect of the grant of patents and applications therefor, and in`
  line `respect of other matters in relation to the grant of patents under this Act, such fees as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a fee is payable in respect of the doing of an act by the Controller, the Controller shall not`
  line `do that act until the fee has been paid.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Where a fee is payable in respect of the filing of a document at the patent office, the fee shall be`
  line `paid along with the document or within the prescribed time and the document shall be deemed not to have`
  line `been filed at the office if the fee has not been paid within such time.]`
  line
  line `(4) Where a principal patent is granted later than two years from the date of filing of ^2[the`
  line `application], the fees which have become due in the meantime may be paid within a term of three months`
  line `from the date of the recording of the patent in the register ^3[or within the extended period not later than`
  line `nine months from the date of recording].`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 71, for "the complete specification" (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 61 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (16020)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 158
  title `Restrictions upon publication of specification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 72, for section 143 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16020&sectionno=143&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `^1[143. Restrictions upon publication of specification.--Subject to the provisions of Chapter VII, an`
  line `application for a patent, and any specification file in pursuance thereof, shall not, except with the consent`
  line `of the applicant, be published by the Controller before the expiration of the period prescribed under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 11A or before the same is open to public inspection in pursuance of sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 11A or section 43.]`
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (16021)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 159
  title `Reports of Examiners to be confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16021&sectionno=144&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `The reports of examiners to the Controller under`
  line `this Act shall not be open to public inspection or be published by the Controller; and such reports shall`
  line `not be liable to production or inspection in any legal proceeding unless the court certifies that the`
  line `production or inspection is desirable in the interests of justice, and ought to be allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (16022)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 160
  title `Publication of official journal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 73, for section 145 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16022&sectionno=145&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `^1[145. Publication of official journal.--The Controller shall publish periodically an official journal`
  line `which shall contain such information as may be required to be published by or under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or any rule made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (16023)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 161
  title `Power of Controller to call for information from patentees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16023&sectionno=146&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller may, at any`
  line `time during the continuance of the patent, by notice in writing, require a patentee or a licensee, exclusive`
  line `or otherwise, to furnish to him within two months from the date of such notice or within such further time`
  line `as the Controller may allow, such information or such periodical statements as to the extent to which the`
  line `patented invention has been commercially worked in India as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), every patentee and every licensee (whether`
  line `exclusive or otherwise) shall furnish in such manner and form and at such intervals (not being less than`
  line `six months) as may be prescribed statements as to the extent to which the patented invention has been`
  line `worked on a commercial scale in India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller may publish the information received by him under sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line `(2) in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (16024)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 162
  title `Evidence of entries, documents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16024&sectionno=147&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) A certificate purporting to be signed by the`
  line `Controller as to any entry, matter or thing which he is authorised by this Act or any rules made thereunder`
  line `to make or do, shall be prima facie evidence of the entry having been made and of the contents thereof`
  line `and of the matter or thing having been done or omitted to be done.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of any entry in any register or of any document kept in the patent office or of any patent,`
  line `or an extract from any such register or document, purporting to be certified by the Controller and sealed`
  line `with the seal of the patent office shall be admitted in evidence in all courts, and in all proceedings,`
  line `without further proof or production of the original.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller or any other officer of the patent office shall not, in any legal proceedings to which`
  line `he is not a party, be compellable to produce the register or any other document in his custody, the`
  line `contents of which can be proved by the production of a certified copy issued under this Act or to appear`
  line `as a witness to prove the matters therein recorded unless by order of the court made for special causes.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (16025)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 163
  title `Declaration by infant, lunatic, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16025&sectionno=148&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person is, by reason of minority, lunacy or other`
  line `disability, incapable of making any statement or doing anything required or permitted by or under this`
  line `Act, the lawful guardian, committee or manager (if any) of the person subject to the disability, or if there`
  line `be none, any person appointed by any court possessing jurisdiction in respect of his property, may make`
  line `such statement or a statement as nearly corresponding thereto as circumstances permit, and do such things`
  line `in the name and on behalf of the person subject to the disability.`
  line
  line `(2) An appointment may be made by the court for the purposes of this section upon the petition of any`
  line `person acting on behalf of the person subject to the disability or of any other person interested in the`
  line `making of the statement or the doing of the thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (16026)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 164
  title `Service of notices, etc., by post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16026&sectionno=149&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Any notice required or authorised to be given by or under this`
  line `Act, and any application or other document so authorised or required to be made or filed, may be given,`
  line `made or filed by post.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (16027)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 165
  title `Security for costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16027&sectionno=150&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `If any party by whom notice of any opposition is given under this Act or by`
  line `whom application is made to the Controller for the grant of a licence under a patent neither resides nor`
  line `carries on business in India, the Controller may require him to give security for the costs of the`
  line `proceedings, and in default of such security being given may treat the opposition or application as`
  line abandoned.
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (16028)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 166
  title `Transmission of orders of courts to Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16028&sectionno=151&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every order of ^1[the High Court ^2***] on a petition for revocation, including orders granting certificates of validity of any`
  line `claim, shall be transmitted by ^1[the High Court ^2***] to the Controller who shall cause`
  line `an entry thereof and reference thereto to be made in the register.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in any suit for infringement of a patent or in any suit under section 106 the validity of any`
  line `claim or a specification is contested and that claim is found by the court to be valid or not valid, as the`
  line `case may be, the court shall transmit a copy of its judgment and decree to the Controller who shall on`
  line `receipt thereof cause an entry in relation to such proceeding to be made in the prescribed manner in a`
  line `supplemental record.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall also apply to the court to which appeals are`
  line `preferred against decisions of ^3[ the courts] referred to in those`
  line sub-sections.
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 74, for the High Court (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The words “or the Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13, for “the Appellate Board or the courts, as the case may be” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 74, ibid., for courts (w.e.f. 2-4-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (16029)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 167
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16029&sectionno=152&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `[Transmission of copies of specification, etc., and inspection thereof.]--Omitted byThe Patents`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2005 (15 of 2005), s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (16030)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 168
  title `Information relating to Patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16030&sectionno=153&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `A person making a request to the Controller in the`
  line `prescribed manner for information relating to any such matters as may be prescribed as respects any`
  line `patent specified in the request or as respects any application for a patent so specified shall be entitled,`
  line `subject to the payment of the prescribed fee, to have information supplied to him accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (16031)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 169
  title `Loss or destruction of Patents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16031&sectionno=154&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `If a patent is lost or destroyed, or its non-production is`
  line `accounted for to the satisfaction of the Controller, the Controller may at any time, on application made in`
  line `the prescribed manner and on payment of the prescribed fee, cause a duplicate thereof to be sealed and`
  line `delivered to the applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (16032)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 170
  title `Reports of Controller to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16032&sectionno=155&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause`
  line `to be placed before both Houses of Parliament once a year a report respecting the execution of this Act by`
  line `or under the Controller.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (16033)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 171
  title `Patent to bind Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16033&sectionno=156&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, a patent`
  line `shall have to all intents the like effect as against Government as it has against any person.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (16034)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 172
  title `Right of Government to sell or use forfeited articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16034&sectionno=157&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the`
  line `power of the Government or of any person deriving title directly or indirectly from the Government to sell`
  line `or use any articles forfeited under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157_a:
  sectionId (16035)
  sectionNo 157A
  orderNo 173
  title `Protection of security of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2002, s.63, for section 157A (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16035&sectionno=157A&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_157_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[157A. Protection of security of India.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the`
  line `Central Government shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not disclose any information relating to any patentable invention or any application relating to`
  line `the grant of patent under this Act, which it considers prejudicial to the interest of the security of India;`
  line
  line `(b) take any action including the revocation of any patent which it considers necessary in the`
  line `interest of the security of India by issue of a notification in the Official Gazette to that effect.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "security of India" include any action`
  line `necessary for the security of India which--`
  line
  line `(i) relates to fissionable materials or the materials from which they are derived; or`
  line
  line `(ii) relates to the traffic in arms, ammunition and implements of war and to such traffic in other`
  line `goods and materials as is carried on directly or indirectly for the purpose of supplying a military`
  line `establishment; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is taken in time of war or other emergency in international relations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (16036)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 174
  title `Power of High Courts to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16036&sectionno=158&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may make rules consistent with this`
  line `Act as to the conduct and procedure in respect of all proceedings before it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (16037)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 175
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16037&sectionno=159&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the Central Government may make`
  line `rules to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner in which any application for a patent, any specifications or drawings and`
  line `any other application or document may be filed in the patent office;`
  line
  line `^1[(ia) the period which the Controller may allow for filing of statement and undertaking for in`
  line `respect of applications under sub-section (1), the period within which the details relating to`
  line `processing of applications may be filed before the Controller and the details to be furnished by the`
  line `applicant to the Controller under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(ib) the period within which a reference to the deposit of materials shall be made in the`
  line `specification under sub-clause (A) of clause (ii) of the proviso to sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(ic) the period for which application for patent shall not be open to the public under sub-section`
  line `(1) and the manner in which the applicant may make a request to the Controller to publish his`
  line `application under subsection (2) of section 11A;`
  line
  line `(id) the manner of making the request for examination for an application for patent and the period`
  line `within which such examination shall be made under sub-sections (1) and (3) of section 11B;`
  line
  line `(ie) the manner in which an application for withdrawal of an application for grant of a patent shall`
  line `be made and the period within which a request for examination from the date of revocation of secrecy`
  line `directions shall be made under the proviso to sub-section (4) of section 11B.]`
  line
  line `(ii) the time within which any act or thing may be done under this Act, including the manner in`
  line `which and the time within which any matter may be ^2[published] under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) the fees which may be payable under this Act and the manner ^3[and time] of payment of such`
  line fees;
  line
  line `(iv) the matters in respect of which the examiner may make a report to the Controller;`
  line
  line `^4[(v) the manner in which and the period within which the Controller shall consider and dispose`
  line `of a representation under sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(va) the period within which the Controller is required to dispose of an application under section`
  line 39;]
  line
  line `(vi) the form and manner in which and the time within which any notice may be given under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(vii) the provisions which may be inserted in an order for restoration of a patent for the protection`
  line `of persons who may have availed themselves of the subject-matter of the patent after the patent had`
  line ceased;
  line
  line `(viii) the establishment of branch offices of the patent office and the regulation generally of the`
  line `business of the patent office, including its branch offices;`
  line
  line `(ix) the maintenance of the register of patents ^3[and the safeguards to be observed in the`
  line `maintenance of such register in computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form] and the`
  line `matters to be entered therein;`
  line
  line `(x) the matters in respect of which the Controller shall have powers of a civil court;`
  line
  line `(xi) the time when and the manner in which the register and any other document open to`
  line `inspection may be inspected under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xii) the qualifications of, and the preparation of a roll of, scientific advisers for the purpose of`
  line `section 115;`
  line
  line ^5****
  line
  line `(xiii) the manner in which any compensation for acquisition by Government of an invention may`
  line `be paid;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the manner in which the register of patent agents may be maintained ^5[under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 125 and the safeguards to be observed in the maintenance of such register of patent agents`
  line `on computer floppies, diskettes or any other electronic form under sub-section (2) of that section] the`
  line `conduct of qualifying examinations for patent agents; and matters connected with their practice and`
  line `conduct, including the taking of disciplinary proceedings against patent agents for misconduct;`
  line
  line `(xv) the regulation of the making, printing, publishing and selling of indexes to, and abridgments`
  line `of, specifications and other documents in the patent office; and the inspection of indexes and`
  line `abridgments and other documents;`
  line
  line `(xvi) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules under this section shall be subject to condition of the rules being made`
  line `after previous publications:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that the circumstances exist which`
  line `render it practically not possible to comply with such condition of previous publication, dispense with`
  line `such compliance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 76, for clauses (ia) and (ib) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for advertised (w.e.f. (1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 38 of 2002, s. 64 (w.e.f. 20-5-2003).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2005, s. 76, for clause (v) (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
  line
  line `5. Clauses (xiia), (xiib) and (xiic) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `6. The proviso added by Act 15 of 2005, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (16038)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 176
  title `Rules to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764&sectionId=16038&sectionno=160&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00002_197039_1517807321764
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or ^1[in two or more successive sessions, and if before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
